(117, 'Feast Offering', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Feast offering day while Shenpen away', 'Feast offering day while Shenpen away.', '2004-10-09T00:00:00'),
(102, 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism month retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'month retreat with Shenpen at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart', '<DIV class=centrecolumn style="LEFT: 1.61%; WIDTH: 98.46%; TOP: 24px; HEIGHT: 1955px">\n<H1>Awakened Heart Sangha</H1>\n<H2>&nbsp;2004 Group Month Retreat<BR><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 0.7em">at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 0.7em">Sat 30th October - Sat 27th November</SPAN></H2>\n<P>In November 2004 Shenpen Hookham will lead a month long retreat at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart in North Wales, UK. Here are some quick notes for anyone is who interested in taking part.</P>\n<H4>What will the retreat involve?</H4>\n<P>The retreat&nbsp;is an opportunity to deepen our meditation, explore our experience, and sharpen our insight. To help us accomplish this we will have:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Many hours of meditation each day \n<LI>Reflection on the course materials from the early part of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism \n<LI>Question &amp; Answer sessions (and possibly teachings) with Shenpen on these topics \n<LI>Personal interviews with Shenpen to discuss our meditation and reflection \n<LI>An atmosphere of silence</LI></UL>\n<H4>What are these course materials we''ll be reflecting on?</H4>\n<P>They''ll be materials from the early part of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, a structured training in Buddhist study, reflection and meditation taught by Shenpen.&nbsp;Topics we''ll focus on at the retreat may include:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Meditation - detailed instructions on the practice of formless meditation \n<LI>Daily life awareness practice - how to carry the quality of awareness we discover in meditation&nbsp;into the rest of our&nbsp;lives \n<LI>Deepening&nbsp;our insight by examining closely our experience&nbsp;and our assumptions about it \n<UL>\n<LI>the space of our awareness -&nbsp;examining the sense we have of thoughts and feelings arising in a kind of space, what we often call ''mind''. Exploring the real nature of this spaciousness - where is it, where are we in relation to it, does it have boundaries? \n<LI>the many aspects of heart - what is our ''heart''? what is it''s nature? how does it relate to ''awareness''? \n<LI>the longing in our hearts - what do we really want? what does it mean to want something? is there anything wrong with wanting?</LI></UL></LI></UL>\n<P>If you want to know more about Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, Shenpen Hookham, and her teaching style, you can read more on the <A href="http://www.ahs.org.uk/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=607">Discovering the Heart of Buddhism pages</A>.</P>\n<H4>Who can&nbsp;take part in&nbsp;the retreat?</H4>\n<P>The retreat is open to anyone whose application to come is accepted by Shenpen. But as a guideline, Shenpen is interested mainly in developing long-term relationships with serious students, so the retreat is intended for:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>people who are already&nbsp;training seriously with&nbsp;Shenpen (enrolled on Discovering the Heart of Buddhism or Members of the Awakened Heart Sangha) \n<LI>people who are considering training seriously with Shenpen (e.g. are considering enrolling on Discovering the Heart of Buddhism).</LI></UL>\n<H4>How much does the retreat cost?</H4>\n<P>So that no one is excluded only for financial reasons, the&nbsp;basic charge&nbsp;for this retreat is&nbsp;just ┬ú13 per night inclusive of food and catering. However, far more than that is really needed to cover the overheads of the Hermitage, so retreatants are asked to make substantial donations in addition to this to help support the Hermitage.&nbsp;Half of these additional donations goes to Shenpen as an offering.</P>\n<H4>Breakdown of weekly costs:</H4>\n<P>1 wk (7 nights) - ┬ú91 &nbsp;/&nbsp;&nbsp;2wks (14 nights) ┬ú182&nbsp; /&nbsp; 3 wks (21 nights) ┬ú273 &nbsp;/&nbsp; 4wks (28 nights) ┬ú351</P>\n<H4>Accommodation for the Retreat</H4>\n<P>Although this is a group retreat most of the meditation periods will be done in retreatants own rooms. It is for this reason that each retreatant will have their own room but will share bathroom facilities with other retreatants. There will be a group meditation morning and evening in the main shrine room where retreatants can connect with there fellow participants and&nbsp;feel the support from others who are doing the same thing.&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<H4>Overseas Travel</H4>\n<P>Note for those&nbsp;considering coming&nbsp;from overseas: the best airport is Manchester (2 hours by train), but London (Heathrow or Gatwick) (5-7 hours by train) are also possible. Flights from the USA to the UK can be had for as low as $200-$400 if you look hard on the internet.</P>\n<H4>Do I have to come for all of the retreat?</H4>\n<P>Shenpen requests that everyone taking part in the retreat comes for the full time if possible. However, if you are already a student of Shenpen''s in the Awakened Heart Sangha, you are allowed to come for just part (at least 1 week) of the retreat if you can''t come to the whole.</P>\n<H4>How to apply&nbsp;to take part in&nbsp;the retreat</H4>\n<P>If you are not already training with Shenpen, you need to learn more about her and her teaching style, to see if this retreat really would suit you:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Read the <A href="http://www.ahs.org.uk/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=607">Discovering the Heart of Buddhism pages</A>&nbsp;to learn more \n<LI>Shenpen actually recommends that you consider enrolling on Discovering the Heart of Buddhism before the retreat begins - the more prepared and focused you are the more you will be able to benefit from the retreat. However, she doesn''t insist on this.</LI></UL>\n<P>Everyone needs to do this:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>Read the Hermitage booklet that describes the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, it''s purpose, spirit, and the retreat boundaries that guide everyone there. \n<LI>Send in to the Hermitage Manager, your answers to the&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=807">Month Retreat Questionnaire</A>, so that Shenpen can learn a bit about you and consider you application. \n<LI>If Shenpen accepts your application, send in a <A href="http://www.ahs.org.uk/media/misc/retreat%20booking%20form.doc" target=_blank>booking form </A>to the Hermitage Manager.</LI></UL>\n<H4>If you have any questions</H4>\n<P>Questions about the practicalities of the retreat and bookings should be sent to Karl, the Hermitage Manager, at <A href="mailto:hermitage@ahs.org.uk">hermitage@ahs.org.uk</A>.</P>\n<P>Questions about whether the retreat is suitable for you should be sent to Shenpen. If you''re not already a student of Shenpen''s and don''t have her contact details, send your questions to Karl and ask him to pass them on.</P>\n<P>If you''re not sure who to ask, ask Karl.</P>\n<P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=707">Introduction to the Hermitage</A> \n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=720">Coming to the Hermitage</A> \n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=723">Supporting the Hermitage</A> \n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=719">Meditation &amp; Feast Offering days</A> \n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=696">November 2004 Month retreat</A> </LI></UL>\n<P></P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P><!-- EnVivo!CS v2.0d-253 --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Time to build page: 0.21875 seconds --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 696 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 34 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 1--><!-- Time to build page: 0.234375 seconds --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 696 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 34 Envivo --></DIV>\n<P><!-- END STRUCTURAL CENTRE COLUMN SEGMENT --><BR clear=all><!-- without this little <br /> NS6 and IE5PC do not stretch the section div down to encopass the column DIVs --><!-- END STRUCTURAL SECTION --><!-- AHS Header --><!-- START STRUCTURAL HEADER --></P>', '2004-10-30T00:00:00'),
(103, 'Christmas & New Year  retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Ten days,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Opportunity to gather and meditate together over Christmas & the new Year. Shenpen may well teach if we beseech her hard enough!', '<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P align=center><IMG height=200 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitageinsnow%20copy.jpg" width=500 align=middle border=0></P>\n<H1><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Christmas and New Year Retreat<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></H1>\n<H2 style="MARGIN: 6pt 0cm 2pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<H2 style="MARGIN: 6pt 0cm 2pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center>North Wales</H2>\n<H2 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">December 23rd 2004 ΓÇô January 2nd 2005<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H2>\n<H2 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H2>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">The Awakened Heart Sangha will be holding a group retreat over the Christmas and New Year holidays for anyone who would like to spend this usually busy period in a relaxed and mostly silent meditative environment with other retreatants.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The retreat will begin at supper on Thursday December 23<SUP>rd</SUP> and end after breakfast on Sunday 2 January. It is fine to come for all or part of the retreat.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">There will be about 6 hours of meditation each day in the shrine room. In the afternoon there will be a group session with stories from the lives of great practitioners and Dharma songs. Hopefully we can also persuade Shenpen to give us teachings on some days. She will definitely give meditation interviews to retreatants. On Christmas day and New YearΓÇÖs Eve we will celebrate with special feast ceremonies.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">Since this is expected to be a small retreat, it will be self-catering. Food will be provided, and the group can decide whether people want to cook individually for themselves or take it in turns to cook for the group.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Costs</H3>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%">Offering to Shenpen</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this retreat other than what she is given as offerings. Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Hermitage costs<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the SanghaΓÇÖs overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"><SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Single Room:<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>┬ú25/night</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"><SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Off-site:<SPAN style="mso-tab-count: 2">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>┬ú20 per day</FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Bursaries<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, or email <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Donation to support Bursary Fund<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;</FONT><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; FONT-VARIANT: small-caps; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">The Venue ΓÇô The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The Christmas retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </FONT></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">How To Book</H3>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20christmas%202004%20(single).doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>.&nbsp; Send your completed form to the address on the form along with your deposit cheque.</P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Questions</H3>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">If you have any questions about this retreat please contact <STRONG>Karl Price, The Hermitage, Ynys Graianog, Criccieth, Gwynedd, LL52 ONT, Tel: (01766) 512 543, email: &nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/hermitage@%20ahs.org.uk">hermitage@ ahs.org.uk</A>.</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL>\n<P></P><!-- LOOPEND -->\n<HR style="DISPLAY: none">\n\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><!-- EnVivo!CS v2.0d-253 --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 1--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo -->&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>', '2004-12-23T00:00:00'),
(369, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2005-04-24T11:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(105, 'The Heart Sutra', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Heart Sutra.  Deepening meditation and daily life awareness practice, and exploring what is meant by the directness of experience with special reference to the Heart Sutra.', '<H1><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><IMG style="WIDTH: 390px; HEIGHT: 280px" height=280 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/events/pic00040%20hermitage%20sh%20pointing%20out%20snowden.jpg" width=140 border=0></SPAN></H1>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">At this year''s spring retreat&nbsp;Shenpen will teach on the Heart Sutra.&nbsp; We will be deepening our meditation and daily life awareness practice and exploring what is meant by the directness of experience with special reference&nbsp;to the Heart Sutra. </FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation.&nbsp; There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informatlly and in discussion groups. There will also be an opportunity for each retreatant to have an individual interview with Shenpen.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The retreat will begin at 6 pm on Saturday,&nbsp;April 30th&nbsp;with a special meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm&nbsp;for everyone. The reteat will end after breakfast on Saturday, May 7th. &nbsp;</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">All meals will be cooked for us, but retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Costs</H3>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%">Offering to Shenpen</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this retreat other than what she is given as offerings. Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Hermitage costs<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha&#039;s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</FONT></P><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">\n<TABLE borderColor=#ffffff cellSpacing=2 cellPadding=2 align=left background="" border=0>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;Single room:</P></TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú37/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Shared room:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú32/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Camping:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú22/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Off-site:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú22/day</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></FONT></P></FONT>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Bursaries<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, or email <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Donation to support Bursary Fund<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"></FONT>&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Help Run this Retreat</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face=Arial>A number of people are needed&nbsp;to manage the running of this retreat, and 50%-100% discounts are available.&nbsp; For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact&nbsp;Jane Powell, on (01970) 880827, </FONT><A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk"><FONT face=Arial>jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</FONT></A><FONT face=Arial>; or Zangmo, on (01580) 240953, </FONT><A href="mailto:zangmo@onetel.com."><FONT face=Arial>zangmo@onetel.com.</FONT></A></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="">&nbsp;<B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; FONT-VARIANT: small-caps; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></FONT></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">The Venue &#150; The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </FONT></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">How To Book</H3>\n<P>Please book your place early, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN APRIL 23rd</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than April 23rd be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20spring%202005%20single.doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>.&nbsp; </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Jane Powell, </STRONG><STRONG>Cynefin, Capel Bangor, Aberystwyth, Ceredigion SY23 3LU </STRONG>.</P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Questions</H3>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">If you have any questions about this retreat please contact: </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>Jane Powell <BR></STRONG><STRONG>Cynefin, <BR>Capel Bangor, <BR>Aberystwyth, <BR>Ceredigion SY23 3LU; </STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>tel: (01970) 880827, (evenings only please);&nbsp;</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>email: <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL>\n<P></P><!-- LOOPEND -->\n<HR style="DISPLAY: none">\n\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><!-- EnVivo!CS v2.0d-253 --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 1--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo -->&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>', '2005-04-30T00:00:00'),
(370, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2005-05-23T15:00:00'),
(106, 'Guru Rinpoche', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Khenpo Tsultrim Gyamtso Rinpoche,Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A retreat on the theme of ''Guru Rinpoche'' with Khenpo Rinpoche and Shenpen Hookham.', '<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4>\n<P><IMG height=145 hspace=45 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/ktgr.jpeg" width=115 align=left border=0></P></FONT></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4>\n<P><IMG style="WIDTH: 123px; HEIGHT: 145px" height=145 hspace=45 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/events/pic00040%20hermitage%20sh%20pointing%20out%20snowden%20-%20cropped%20small.jpg" width=115 align=right border=0></P></FONT></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4>\n<P>&nbsp;</P></FONT></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4>\n<P>&nbsp;</P></FONT></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4>\n<P>&nbsp;</P></FONT></SPAN>\n<P align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<P align=center><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 20pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT color=#00008b size=4></FONT></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<P><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"><FONT face=Verdana>The Awakened Heart Sangha is once again delighted to welcome Khenpo Rinpoche to teach during our week-long Summer Retreat at the Hermitage.&nbsp; We are doubly fortunate in that Shenpen will teach us on those days that Rinpoche does not teach, i.e. at the beginning and end of the retreat.</FONT></P>\n<P>Khenpo Rinpoche is one of the foremost living teachers of the Mahamudra and Dzogchen tradition of Tibetan Buddhism, a great scholar and master of meditation.&nbsp; Rinpoche is often compared to the great yogin Milarepa: he has no fixed abode, few possessions, and has meditated for years in solitude, sometimes sealed in darkness.&nbsp; Like Milarepa, he is known for his spontaneous songs of realisation that offer insight into the true nature of reality.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">The theme of this year''s retreat is ''Guru Rinpoche'', also known as&nbsp;Padmasambhava, or the Lotus Born, who brought Buddhism&nbsp;to Tibet.&nbsp;Guru Rinpoche&nbsp;is a powerful, esoteric, mystical and enlightened figure, who is considered to be a manifestation of the Buddha and whose miraculous life spanned several centuries, making him something much more than the usual historical figure. Guru Rinpoche&nbsp;is particularly important for our Lineage, and he is&nbsp;considered to appear today "in any form we need" to help us on the Path.&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><BR>This will be a week to steep ourselves in the tradition of Guru Rinpoche&nbsp;and to explore what it might mean to us in this day and age, using teachings, stories, songs and imagery. In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation.&nbsp;There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups. </P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</P></FONT>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Dates</H3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">\n<P>The full retreat will begin at 6 pm on Saturday, June 18th&nbsp;with a special meeting with Shenpen for any newcomers, followed by supper at&nbsp;7 pm for everyone.&nbsp; The retreat will end before lunch on Saturday,&nbsp;June 25th.&nbsp; </P>\n<P>Rinpoche will&nbsp;arrive on&nbsp;Monday, June 20th to give his first teaching after supper, and will&nbsp;depart on Friday morning,&nbsp;June 24th . </P></FONT>\n<H3>Costs</H3>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Offerings to Rinpoche and Shenpen<BR><BR></H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><FONT size=3><FONT size=2>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Everyone attending the retreat is asked to make a donation as an offering for Rinpoche and Shenpen. People can choose whether to specify how much of their offering they wish to donate to each teacher or just make a single donation to be divided as deemed appropriate by the organisers. Suggested amount: ┬ú50-┬ú200<SPAN class=MsoCommentReference><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt"><A style="mso-comment-reference: JS_1"></A></SPAN></SPAN></FONT>.</FONT></P><FONT face="Trebuchet MS"></FONT>\n<DIV style="mso-element: comment"><SPAN style="mso-comment-author: ''Jonathan Shaw''"><A name=_msocom_1></A></SPAN>&nbsp;</DIV>\n<H4 language=JavaScript class=MsoCommentText onmouseover="msoCommentShow(''_anchor_1'',''_com_1'')" style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Hermitage costs</SPAN></H4>\n<P language=JavaScript class=MsoCommentText onmouseover="msoCommentShow(''_anchor_1'',''_com_1'')" style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">This amount goes entirely towards catering and accommodation costs,&nbsp;the extra cost in hosting Rinpoche, plus an amount to&nbsp;offset the Sangha&#039;s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P>\n<P language=JavaScript class=MsoCommentText onmouseover="msoCommentShow(''_anchor_1'',''_com_1'')" style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">\n<TABLE borderColor=#ffffff cellSpacing=2 cellPadding=2 align=left background="" border=0>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;Single room:</P></TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú42/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Shared room:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú35/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Camping:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú24/night</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Off-site (with meals):</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú24/day</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Off-site (no meals):</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú20/day</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></P>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><BR><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Bursaries<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, or email <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P>\n<H4 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><BR><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">Donation to support Bursary Fund<o:p></o:p></SPAN></H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">How To Book</H3>\n<P><FONT face="">Accommodation at the Hermitage is limited, so you are advised to book early for this popular retreat.&nbsp; You may come for part of the retreat, but priority will be given to those booking for the entire retreat.&nbsp; </FONT></P>\n<P>Please book your place early, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN JUNE 8th </B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than June 8th be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P><FONT face="">Anyone planning&nbsp;to&nbsp;book&nbsp;just for those days&nbsp;that Khenpo Rinpoche is teaching&nbsp;is requested to arrive between 4:00 and 6:00pm on June 20th and to depart between 11:00am and noon on the 24th.</FONT></P>\n<P>You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20summer%202005%20single.doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>.&nbsp; </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Lesley Rhodes,</STRONG> <STRONG>''Sonam Ling'', 22 King Edward''s Road, Malvern Wells, WR14 4AJ. </STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P></FONT>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Help Run this Retreat</H3>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Service Rota</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Our meals will be cooked for us, but all retreatants will be expected to&nbsp;help out with the various other tasks involved in the smooth running of the retreat: assisting in the kitchen, washing up,&nbsp;hosting Khenpo Rinpoche, tending the shrine room,&nbsp;and cleaning up at the end of the retreat, for example. In particular, this is a wonderful opportunity to directly serve and make a strong connection with as distinguished a teacher as Khenpo Rinpoche. There will be a rota with these and other tasks that everyone can sign up on. <BR></P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Managing the Retreat</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="">A number of people are needed&nbsp;to manage the running of this retreat, and 50%-100% discounts are available.&nbsp; For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact&nbsp;Jane Powell, on (01970) 880827, </FONT><A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk"><FONT face="">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</FONT></A><FONT face="">; or Zangmo, on (01580) 240953, </FONT><A href="mailto:zangmo@onetel.com."><FONT face="">zangmo@onetel.com.</FONT></A></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;</FONT><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; FONT-VARIANT: small-caps; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">The Venue &#150; The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans. There is&nbsp;space for camping in one of the large fields at the Hermitage.</FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face="">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </FONT></P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><FONT face=""></FONT>&nbsp;</H3>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Questions</H3>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">If you have any questions about this retreat please contact: </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>Lesley Rhodes,</STRONG> <BR><STRONG>''Sonam Ling'', <BR>22 King Edward''s Road, <BR>Malvern Wells, WR14 4AJ. </STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>tel: 01684 573737.&nbsp;</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"><STRONG>email: <A href="mailto:lesley@shiel289.freeserve.co.uk">lesley@shiel289.freeserve.co.uk</A>.</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 125%; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H3>Links to Further Information</H3>\n<H4>About Awakened Heart Sangha retreats: </H4><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A><BR></LI></UL></FONT></FONT>\n<H4 dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">About Khenpo Rinpoche:</H4><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">\n<P dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">For further information about Khenpo Rinpoche, you&nbsp;might want to look at&nbsp;his website <FONT face=Arial><A href="http://www.ktgrinpoche.org/">http://www.ktgrinpoche.org</A>, </FONT>which nearer the time will have details of&nbsp;all his&nbsp;UK stops&nbsp;for 2005<FONT face=Arial color=#0000ff>.&nbsp; <FONT face=Verdana><FONT color=#000000>Details as we</FONT> <FONT color=#000000>know them now are:</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px"><FONT face=Tahoma><FONT face=Arial size=2><SPAN class=571232912-14012005><FONT color=#000000 size=2>Friday 10th - Wednesday 15th June: Course on Holy Island<BR>Friday 17th - Sunday 19th June: Course in Samye Ling<BR>Friday 24th - Sunday 26th June: Course in Samye Dzong London<BR></P></BLOCKQUOTE></FONT></SPAN></FONT></FONT>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P></P><!-- LOOPEND -->\n<HR style="DISPLAY: none">\n\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><!-- EnVivo!CS v2.0d-253 --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 2--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo --><!-- Iterations though FinalizeHTML function: 3--><!-- Number of current recursive calls in the stack to FinalizeHTML function: 1--><!-- Time to build page: 0.15625 seconds --><!-- Cache:  SELECT * FROM articles LEFT JOIN (SELECT titleID, title AS teaching_title, abstract AS teaching_briefsummary, article AS teaching_fullsummary, author AS teaching_teacher, datecreated AS teaching_date, datecreated AS datecreated, classifications AS teaching_classifications, event AS teaching_event FROM articles JOIN (SELECT TID AS titleID, convert(int, title) AS titleInt FROM (SELECT ID AS TID, title, ISNUMERIC(title) AS Num FROM articles) ChkNum WHERE ChkNum.Num = 1) TitleInts On articles.ID = TitleInts.TitleInt) teachings ON articles.ID = teachings.titleID WHERE articles.ID = 939 AND convert(datetime,convert(varchar,getdate())) BETWEEN articles.startdate AND articles.enddate Envivo --><!-- Database:  SELECT * FROM categories WHERE ID = 33 Envivo -->&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', '2005-06-18T00:00:00'),
(436, 'Talk to long retreatants', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Single session,Teachings', 'Rigdzin Shikpo Rinpoche', '', '', '2005-06-26T15:00:00'),
(113, 'Spiritual Friend', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Spiritual Friend.  An exploration of the importance of spiritual friendship with reference to Sutra material, especially the Gandhavyuha (3rd volume of Flower Ornament Sutra).', '<P>At this year''s&nbsp;Autumn retreat,&nbsp;Lama Shenpen will teach on the the importance of spiritual friendship with reference to Sutra material, especially the Gandhavyuha (3rd volume of the Flower Ornament Sutra).&nbsp; We will be deepening our meditation and daily life awareness practice and exploring what is meant by the directness of experience with special reference&nbsp;to the Gandhavyuha. </P>\n<P>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation.&nbsp; There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informatlly and in discussion groups. There will also be an opportunity for each retreatant to have an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6 pm on Saturday,&nbsp;September 17th with a special meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm&nbsp;for everyone. The reteat will end after breakfast on Saturday, September 24th. &nbsp;</P>\n<P>All meals will be cooked for us, but retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<P>Costs</P>\n<P>Offering to&nbsp; Lama Shenpen</P>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose. </P>\n<P>&nbsp;&nbsp; Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P>\n<P>Retreat&nbsp;costs</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P>\n<P>\n<P>&nbsp;Single room:</P>&nbsp;┬ú37/night &nbsp;Shared room: &nbsp;┬ú32/night &nbsp;Camping: &nbsp;┬ú22/night &nbsp;Off-site: &nbsp;┬ú22/day \n<P></P>\n<P>Bursaries</P>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, or email cindy@ahs.org.uk, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P>\n<P>Donation to support Bursary Fund</P>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P>\n<P>Help Run this Retreat</P>\n<P>A number of people are needed&nbsp;to manage the running of this retreat, and 50%-100% discounts are available.&nbsp; For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact&nbsp;Jane Powell, on (01970) 880827, jpowell@ukonline.co.uk.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;<B>&nbsp;</B></P>\n<P>The Venue &#150; The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </P>\n<P>How To Book</P>\n<P>Please book your place early, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN September 7th</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than April 23rd be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P>You may download a booking form from this website by&nbsp;clicking here.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to Jessica Parkes, 32 Green Lane, Ockbrook, Derbyshire DE72 3SE.</P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<P>Questions</P>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat please contact: </P>\n<P>Jessica Parkes 32 Green Lane Ockbrook,Derbyshire DE72 3SE</P>\n<P>Tel: 01332 544483</P>\n<P>email: Jessica@ahs.org.uk</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<P>Frequently Asked Questions about retreats. \n<P>The booklet "An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</P>', '2005-09-17T00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(115, 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism - Confidence and Heart Wish', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism. Working in depth with Discovering the Heart of Buddhism Course Book Two and working individually with Shenpen to deepen your meditation using instructions based on Tashi Namgyal''s "Clarifying the Natural State" and other Mahamudra texts including Milarepa Songs.', '<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt" align=center><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<IMG src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitage_hills.jpg" align=textTop border=0><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This autumn Lama Shenpen Hookham will lead a month-long retreat at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart in North Wales, UK.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This retreat is a unique opportunity to take an extended period of time to deepen our meditation and daily life awareness practice, explore our experience, and sharpen our insight, all in the supportive atmosphere of a group retreat. We will be particularly reflecting on the course materials in Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, Book 2 &#150; Confidence and Heart Wish.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">While retreatants are encouraged to have completed Book 1 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, this is not a requirement for attendance. Lama Shenpen''s teachings offer ''spiral learning'', whereby we hear the core teachings over and over again, each time deepening our understanding of all the inter-related aspects. So the teachings on this retreat can be heard and understood in a whole new way by experienced practitioners and new students alike.</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The retreat will involve:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Many hours of meditation each day<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">Detailed instructions on the practice of formless meditation</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Reflection on the course materials from Book 2 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Teachings and Question &amp; Answer sessions with Lama Shenpen on these topics<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Personal interviews with Lama Shenpen to discuss our meditation and reflection<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">An atmosphere of silence<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Accommodation for the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Although this is a group retreat most of the meditation periods will be done in retreatants'' own rooms. It is for this reason that each retreatant will have his or her own room but will share bathroom facilities with other retreatants. While there will be extended periods of solitary meditation and silence, there will also be times when retreatants can connect with their fellow participants and feel the support from others who are doing the same thing. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Dharma Work on the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including helping in the kitchen, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Do I have to come for all of the retreat?</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Lama Shenpen requests that everyone taking part in the retreat come for the full time if possible, and priority will be given to those booking for the entire retreat. However, if you can''t come to the whole retreat and there is room available, you will be allowed to come for just part, provided you can come for at least 1 week and provided you can be there for the first week. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT size=4>Costs<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H3>\n<P style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Offering to Lama Shenpen </H4>\n<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm"><EM>Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200 per week</EM></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm"><EM></EM>&nbsp;</P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Retreat costs</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%; tab-stops: 14.2pt 134.7pt">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of running the Hermitage, catering, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. </P></SPAN>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;</SPAN>&nbsp; \n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 425px; HEIGHT: 141px" align=left>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Early Bird Discount:&nbsp; </TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú693/whole month if you book by Oct 1</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Otherwise:</TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú770/whole month or<BR>&nbsp;┬ú35/night for the first 7 nights<BR>&nbsp;┬ú25/night for subsequent nights</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Off-site:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú15/day</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H6><FONT color=#000000></FONT>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H4>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4>Bursaries</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, or email <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H4>Donation to Support the Bursary Fund</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H3>Help Run this Retreat</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">A number of people are needed&nbsp;to manage the running of this retreat, and discounts are available.&nbsp; For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact&nbsp;Jane Powell, on (01970) 880827, </SPAN><A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk"><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</SPAN></A><SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">;</SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H3>The Venue &#150; The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H3>Travel information</H3>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Note for those&nbsp;considering coming&nbsp;from overseas: the nearest airports are Birmingham and Manchester (2-4 hours by train), but London (Heathrow or Gatwick) (5-7 hours by train) is also possible.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H3>How to Book</H3><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">There are limited places on this retreat, so please book early. You will receive a substantial discount if you book for the whole month by October 1. <STRONG>The last date we will accept bookings is OCTOBER 25th</STRONG>. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20nov%20month%202005%20single.doc" target=_blank>clicking here.</A></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to: Cindy Cooper, 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or putting you on a waiting list or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">If you have any questions about this retreat please contact: </P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%"><STRONG>Cindy Cooper <BR><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><STRONG>99 Warwick Way<BR>London SW1V1QL</STRONG> </SPAN></STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%"><STRONG><SPAN style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><BR><STRONG>Tel: (020) 7834-5367 <BR>email:</STRONG> </SPAN>cindy@ahs.org.uk</STRONG></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0cm" type=circle>\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>.<o:p></o:p></SPAN> \n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></LI></UL>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN></SPAN></P>', '2005-11-05T00:00:00'),
(122, 'Feast Offering', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Feast your senses and explore the dynamic at play the Feast Offering&#151;a special theme for the festive season.', '<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P align=left><IMG height=222 hspace=0 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitageinsnow%20copy.jpg" width=644 align=absMiddle border=0></P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Theme</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P align=justify>This retreat is geared towards all students currently studying with Lama Shenpen.&nbsp; The theme of this week-long retreat will be Feast Offering. We will explore the importance of the idea of centrality of offering with reference to the Shrimala Mahayana Feast Offering liturgy, the Feast Offering booklet and the Seven Branch Prayer.</P>\n<P>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation.&nbsp; There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups. There will also be an opportunity for each retreatant to have an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P><FONT face="Lucida Sans" color=#0000cd size=2>\n<P><STRONG>Arrival and Departure Times</STRONG></P></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6pm on Wednesday,&nbsp;December 23rd&nbsp;with a special meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm&nbsp;for everyone. The retreat will end after breakfast on Friday, January 2nd.</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P><FONT color=#0000cd>Other Retreat Activities</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>A common experience on Buddhist retreats is Meditation, Study and Dharma in Action! Awakened Heart Sangha retreats engage us fully in this &#151; all retreatants help with various tasks that help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer; you know, chopping wood and carrying water!</P>\n<P><STRONG><FONT color=#0000cd>Costs</FONT></STRONG></P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P><FONT color=#0000cd>Offering to Lama Shenpen</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Lama Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this week other than what she is given as offerings. <I>Suggested amount:</FONT><FONT size=1> </FONT><FONT size=1>┬ú50-200</FONT></I></P><FONT size=1><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P><FONT color=#0000cd><EM>Hermitage costs</EM></FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P><EM>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of running the Hermitage, catering and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. </EM></P>\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ┬ú37/night</P>\n<P>Shared room:&nbsp; ┬ú32/night</P>\n<P>Camping (!):&nbsp;&nbsp; ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>Offsite:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ┬ú22/day</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Bursary Fund</FONT> </P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Belinda Wain at Llwyn Eilian, Rhosgadfan, Caernarfon, Gwynedd, LL54 7HE, or email belinda@ahs.org.uk, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Help run this retreat</FONT> </P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>A number of people are needed to manage the running of this retreat. For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact the Events Coordinator, Jane Powell, on 01970 880827, <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.<FONT size=1></P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Venue &#150; the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P align=justify>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn Peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">How To Book</H3>\n<P>Please book your place early, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN December 7th</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than December 7th, be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/christmas%2005%20bkg%20form%20word.doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>.&nbsp; </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Belinda Wain, Llwyn Eilian, Rhosgadfan, Caernarfon, Gwynedd, LL54 7HE</STRONG>.</P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<P><STRONG><FONT face="Lucida Sans">&nbsp;</FONT><FONT color=#0000cd>Questions</FONT></STRONG></P><FONT size=1>\n<P>If you have any questions about the retreat you can contact Jane Powell by phone on 01970 880827 or at: </P>\n<P>Cynefin, Capel Bangor, Aberystwyth, Ceredigion, SY23 3LU </P>\n<P>or email: <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</P>\n<P><FONT face="Times New Roman" size=3></FONT></P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT>', '2005-12-23T00:00:00'),
(129, 'Sangha Training Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Restricted retreat for long-term committed members of the Awakened Heart Sangha.', '<P><FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #f4f4f4">This is a restricted retreat for long-term committed members of the Awakened Heart Sangha.</FONT></P>\n<P><FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #f4f4f4">If you would like to apply to come on the retreat, please email Lama Shenpen.</FONT></P>\n<P><FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #f4f4f4">If you have questions about the retreat, email Katie at <A href="mailto:katie@ahs.org.uk">katie@ahs.org.uk</A> or call her&nbsp;on 0870&nbsp;774 3580 .</FONT></P>\n<P><FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #f4f4f4">If you have been accepted to the retreat and wish to book, email Belinda at <A href="mailto:belinda@ahs.org.uk">belinda@ahs.org.uk</A> or call her&nbsp;on 01286 831 628.</FONT></P>', '2006-04-22T00:00:00'),
(133, 'KTGR Waiting List', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Khenpo Tsultrim Gyamtso Rinpoche', '', 'Please disregard this listing. It is no longer valid and will be deleted. Thank you.', '2006-06-01T00:00:00'),
(131, 'The Songs of Milarepa', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week of meditation and teachings by Lama Shenpen on the life and songs of Milarepa, the Tibetan poet saint. Open to all, this is an opportunity to connect with the warm-hearted and profound songs of one of the key teachers of the Kagyu lineage. Lama Shenpen will be relating these songs to the way we practice in the Awakened Heart Sangha.', '<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 13pt; FONT-FAMILY: Perpetua; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN></P>\n<P><IMG height=335 hspace=0 src="http://www.ahs.org.uk/images/mila.jpg" width=227 border=2>&nbsp; A week of meditation and teachings by Lama Shenpen on the life and songs of&nbsp;Milarepa,&nbsp;Tibet''s poet saint. Open to all, this is an opportunity to connect with the warm-hearted and profound songs of one of the key teachers of the Kagyu lineage. Lama Shenpen will be relating these songs to the way we practice in the Awakened Heart Sangha.</P>\n<P>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation.&nbsp; There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups. There will also be an opportunity for each retreatant to have an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6 pm on Saturday,&nbsp;June 17th with a special meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm&nbsp;for everyone. The retreat will formally end after breakfast on Saturday,&nbsp;June 24th. &nbsp;Following the retreat, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H3><FONT color=#ff0000>Costs</FONT></H3>\n<P>Offering to&nbsp; Lama Shenpen:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose. </P>\n<P>Retreat&nbsp;costs</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P>\n<P>\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night &nbsp;</P>\n<P>Shared room: &nbsp;┬ú32/night &nbsp;</P>\n<P>Offsite or Camping: &nbsp;┬ú22/day</P>\n<H3><FONT color=#ff0000>The Venue &#150; The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</FONT></H3>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book. </P>\n<H3><FONT color=#ff0000>How To Book</FONT></H3>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN&nbsp;June 7th</B>.</P>\n<P>You may&nbsp;request a booking form by emailing <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A> &nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth, LL52 0AR.</P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H3><FONT color=#ff0000>Questions</FONT></H3>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat please contact: </P>\n<P><A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A> </P>\n<P>Tel: 0870 7743580</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<P>Frequently Asked Questions about retreats. \n<P>The booklet "An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</P>\n<H3><FONT color=#ff0000>Bursaries</FONT></H3>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<P>Donation to support Bursary Fund</P>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P>', '2006-06-17T00:00:00'),
(135, 'Going Deeper: A Meditation Intensive', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Spend a week in intensive meditation with other practitioners and receive meditation teachings and instruction from Lama Shenpen. This contemplative retreat is different from a regular teaching retreat. With more time and space for reflection and meditation, you might find your practice stabilising and growing stronger.', '<H2>Intensive Meditation Week Retreat </H2>\n<H2>August 19-26, 2006</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P>Spend a week in intensive meditation with other practitioners and receive meditation teachings and instruction from Lama Shenpen. This contemplative retreat is different from a regular teaching retreat. With more time and space for reflection and meditation, you might find your practice stabilising and growing stronger.</P>\n<P>Silence will be observed most of the time. Each retreatant will have an opportunity for an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P>\n<H5>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H5>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6 pm on Saturday,&nbsp;August 19th with a meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm&nbsp;for everyone. The retreat will formally end after breakfast on Saturday,&nbsp;August 26th. &nbsp;Following the retreat, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN&nbsp;August 7th</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/booking%20form%20summer-autumn%2006.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth, LL52 0AR. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 0870 7743580.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>', '2006-08-19T00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(137, 'Openness & Clarity: A Month Retreat Exploring DHB Book 3', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'This year''s month retreat will explore the third book of the Discovering the Heart of Buddhism course, focusing on Openness and Clarity. These month-long explorations enable participants to uncover more and more significance and inspiration within the course as well as deepen their meditation practice.', '<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN>Book&nbsp;3: Openness and Clarity</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>Month retreat at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>October 7-November 4, 2006 </FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">**Please note the dates have changed**</SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<IMG src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitage_hills.jpg" align=textTop border=0><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This year''s month retreat will explore the third book of the Discovering the Heart of Buddhism course, focusing on Openness and Clarity. These month-long explorations enable participants to uncover more and more significance and inspiration within the course as well as deepen their meditation practice.&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This retreat is a unique opportunity to&nbsp;devote an extended period of time to&nbsp;our meditation and daily life awareness practice, explore our experience, and sharpen our insight, all in the supportive atmosphere of a group retreat. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">While retreatants are encouraged to have completed Book 1 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, this is not a requirement for attendance. Lama Shenpen''s teachings offer ''spiral learning'', whereby we hear the core teachings over and over again, each time deepening our understanding of all the inter-related aspects. So the teachings on this retreat can be heard and understood in a whole new way by experienced practitioners and new students alike.</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The retreat will involve:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Many hours of meditation each day<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">Detailed instructions on the practice of formless meditation</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Reflection on the course materials from Book 2 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Teachings and Question &amp; Answer sessions with Lama Shenpen on these topics<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Personal interviews with Lama Shenpen to discuss our meditation and reflection<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">An atmosphere of silence<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Accommodation for the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Although this is a group retreat, most of the meditation periods will be done in retreatants'' own rooms. It is for this reason that each retreatant will have his or her own room with shared bathroom facilities. While there will be extended periods of solitary meditation and silence, there will also be times when retreatants can connect with their fellow participants and feel the support from others who are doing the same thing. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Dharma Work on the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including helping in the kitchen, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Do I have to come for all of the retreat?</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Lama Shenpen requests that everyone taking part in the retreat come for the full time if possible, and priority will be given to those booking for the entire retreat. If you cannot come to the whole retreat, and if there is room available,&nbsp; you will be allowed to come for just part, provided you can come for at least 1 week and provided you can be there for the first week. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT size=4>Costs<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H3>\n<P style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Offering to Lama Shenpen </H4>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose. </SPAN><EM>Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200 per week</EM></P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<H5 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm">Retreat costs</H5>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%; tab-stops: 14.2pt 134.7pt">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of running the Hermitage, catering, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. </P></SPAN>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;</SPAN>&nbsp; \n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 425px; HEIGHT: 141px" align=left>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Early Bird Discount:&nbsp; </TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú693 if you book by&nbsp;September 8</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Otherwise:</TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú770/whole month, or<BR>&nbsp;┬ú35/night for the first 7 nights, and <BR>&nbsp;┬ú25/night for subsequent nights</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Off-site:</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;┬ú15/day</TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 6pt 0.5in; tab-stops: 5.75in">\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></SPAN></SPAN><o:p></o:p></P>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p> \n<P></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H6><FONT color=#000000></FONT>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H4>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Travel information</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Note for those&nbsp;considering coming&nbsp;from overseas: the nearest airports are Birmingham and Manchester (2-4 hours by train), but London (Heathrow or Gatwick) (5-7 hours by train) is also possible.</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</H5>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">How to Book</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">There are limited places on this retreat, so please book early. You will receive a substantial discount if you book for the whole month by&nbsp;September 8. <STRONG>The last date we will accept bookings is&nbsp;October 2nd</STRONG>. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/booking%20form%20summer-autumn%2006.doc">clicking here</A><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20nov%20month%202005%20single.doc" target=_blank>.</A>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to: Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth, Gwynedd, LL52 0AR.&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or putting you on a waiting list or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">If you have any questions about this retreat please email <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A>. </P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0cm" type=circle>\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>.<o:p></o:p></SPAN> \n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></LI></UL>\n<H5 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Bursaries</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary email <A href="mailto:bursaries@ahs.org.uk">bursaries@ahs.org.uk</A> .</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Donation to Support the Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednyfed, Criccieth LL52 0AR</P><o:p></o:p></SPAN>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN></SPAN></P>', '2006-10-07T00:00:00'),
