(155, 'The Buddha Within', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'restricted teachings on The Buddha Within', '&nbsp;restricted teachings on The Buddha Within', '2007-02-22T00:00:00'),
(146, 'Sangha Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A retreat for committed members of the Awakened Heart Sangha.', '<FONT style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: #f4f4f4">\n<H2>Sangha Retreat</H2>\n<H2>21-28 April&nbsp;2007</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P>This retreat is restricted to committed members of the Awakened Heart Sangha. If you would like more information and an application to attend, email Katie Morrow at <A href="mailto:katie@ahs.org.uk">katie@ahs.org.uk</A></P>\n<P><FONT color=#191970><STRONG>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</STRONG></FONT></P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;March 1</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>\n<P></FONT>&nbsp;</P>', '2007-04-21T00:00:00'),
(373, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2007-05-02T19:35:00'),
(147, 'Guru Rinpoche Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week retreat on Padmasambhava--Guru Rinpoche', '<h2>Guru Rinpoche Retreat</h2>\n<h2>16-23 June 2007</h2>\n<h2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</h2>\n<p>The aim of this retreat is to deepen and strengthen our connection with Guru Rinpoche. Lama Shenpen will guide us in considering what he represents to us as the essence of our lineage, what his story means and how it is relevant to us today. His story carries adhistana to help our practice by removing obstacles and helping deep understanding and love to arise in our hearts. How is all this possible? What is this power that Guru Rinpoche and his lineage have and how does that connect us to our own power to remove the sufferings of ourselves and others?</p>\n<h5>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</h5>\n<p>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</p>\n<p>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book.</p>\n<p>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</p>\n<p>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</p>\n<h5>Costs</h5>\n<p>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</p>\n<p>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</p>\n<blockquote style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px" dir="ltr">\n<p>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ├»┬┐┬╜50-200</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Accomodation</p>\n<blockquote style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px" dir="ltr">\n<p>Single room:&nbsp;├»┬┐┬╜37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ├»┬┐┬╜32; Camping or off-site: ├»┬┐┬╜22/night</p>\n<p>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h5>How To Book</h5>\n<p>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<strong>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;June 1</strong>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<a href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</p>\n<h5>Questions</h5>\n<p>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</p>\n<p>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <a href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</a> about retreats or the booklet <a href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</a>.</p>\n<h5>Bursaries</h5>\n<p>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</p>\n<h5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</h5>\n<p>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</p>\n<p>A week-long retreat on Guru Rinpoche at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart.</p>', '2007-06-16T00:00:00'),
(374, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2007-07-28T18:00:00'),
(375, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2007-07-29T16:07:00'),
(148, 'Meditation Intensive: Turning the Mind from Samsara', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week of meditation and teaching', '<H2>Meditation Intensive</H2>\n<H2>August 25 to September 1, 2007</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P>Spend a week in intensive meditation with other practitioners and receive meditation teachings and instruction from Lama Shenpen. This contemplative retreat is different from a regular teaching retreat. With more time and space for reflection and meditation, you might find your practice stabilising and growing stronger.</P>\n<P>Silence will be observed most of the time. Each retreatant will have an opportunity for an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P>\n<H5>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H5>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;August 7th</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 0870 7743580.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>', '2007-08-25T00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(149, 'Sensitivity and Mandala: A Month Retreat on DHB 4', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Month retreat on DHB 4', '<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN>Book&nbsp;4: Sensitivity and Mandala</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>Month retreat at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>29 September to 27 October</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<IMG src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitage_hills.jpg" align=textTop border=0><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This year''s month retreat will explore the&nbsp;fourth book of the Discovering the Heart of Buddhism course, focusing on Sensitivity and Mandala. This month-long exploration will enable participants to uncover more and more significance and inspiration within the course as well as deepen their meditation practice.&nbsp;</SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This retreat is a unique opportunity to&nbsp;devote an extended period of time to&nbsp;our meditation and daily life awareness practice, explore our experience, and sharpen our insight, all in the supportive atmosphere of a group retreat. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">While retreatants are encouraged to have completed Book 1 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, this is not a requirement for attendance. Lama Shenpen''s teachings offer ''spiral learning'', whereby we hear the core teachings over and over again, each time deepening our understanding of all the inter-related aspects. So the teachings on this retreat can be heard and understood in a whole new way by experienced practitioners and new students alike.</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The retreat will involve:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Many hours of meditation each day<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">Detailed instructions on the practice of formless meditation</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Reflection on the course materials from Book&nbsp;4 of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Teachings and Question &amp; Answer sessions with Lama Shenpen on these topics<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Personal interviews with Lama Shenpen to discuss our meditation and reflection</SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">An atmosphere of silence<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Note on Changes to Format of Retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><FONT color=#000000>The teaching part of the retreat will formally end on Friday 18 October. The following week, from&nbsp;October 19 to the 27, will be an opportunity for retreatants to deepen their understanding through individual practice and discussion, but Lama Shenpen will not be in residence. During the first three weeks of the retreat, Lama Shenpen will be giving teachings on most days--so the overall number of talks will be about the same as in previous month retreats. </FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><FONT color=#000000>The reason for making this change is two-fold. Firstly, we have received feedback from previous retreatants that they would benefit from more time at the end of the retreat to absorb what they have received. Secondly, Lama Shenpen has a special opportunity to receive some NVC training herself during the last week of October. <BR></FONT></P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Accommodation for the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Although this is a group retreat, most of the meditation periods will be done in retreatants'' own rooms. It is for this reason that each retreatant will have his or her own room with shared bathroom facilities. While there will be extended periods of solitary meditation and silence, there will also be times when retreatants can connect with their fellow participants and feel the support from others who are doing the same thing. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Dharma Work on the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including helping in the kitchen, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Do I have to come for all of the retreat?</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Lama Shenpen requests that everyone taking part in the retreat come for the full time if possible, and priority will be given to those booking for the entire retreat. If you cannot come to the whole retreat, and if there is room available,&nbsp; you will be allowed to come for just part, provided you can come for at least 1 week and provided you can be there for the first week. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT size=4>Costs<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H3>\n<P style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Offering to Lama Shenpen </H4>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose. </SPAN><EM>Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200 per week</EM></P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<H5 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm">Retreat costs</H5>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%; tab-stops: 14.2pt 134.7pt">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of running the Hermitage, catering, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P></SPAN>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;</SPAN>&nbsp; \n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 425px; HEIGHT: 141px" align=left>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Early Bird Discount:&nbsp; </TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú693 if you book by&nbsp;1 August</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Otherwise:</TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú770/whole month, or<BR>&nbsp;┬ú35/night for the first 7 nights, and <BR>&nbsp;┬ú25/night for subsequent nights</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD></TD>\n<TD></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 6pt 0.5in; tab-stops: 5.75in">\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''"></SPAN></SPAN><o:p></o:p></P>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p> \n<P></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H6><FONT color=#000000></FONT>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H4>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Travel information</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Note for those&nbsp;considering coming&nbsp;from overseas: the nearest airports are Birmingham and Manchester (2-4 hours by train), but London (Heathrow or Gatwick) (5-7 hours by train) is also possible.</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</H5>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">How to Book</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">There are limited places on this retreat, so please book early. You will receive a substantial discount if you book for the whole month by&nbsp;1 August. <STRONG>The last date we will accept bookings is&nbsp;22 September</STRONG>. You may download a booking form by clicking <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here.</A></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You may&nbsp;request a booking form by emailing <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A> &nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to: Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN. &nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or putting you on a waiting list or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">If you have any questions about this retreat please email <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A>. </P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0cm" type=circle>\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>.<o:p></o:p></SPAN> \n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></LI></UL>\n<H5 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Bursaries</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary email <A href="mailto:bursaries@ahs.org.uk">bursaries@ahs.org.uk</A> .</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Donation to Support the Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth LL52 0RN</P></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>', '2007-09-29T00:00:00'),
(376, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2008-03-22T01:24:00'),
(157, 'Sangha Retreat: Values and Guardianship', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Annual Sangha Training Retreat', '<H1>&nbsp;Sangha Retreat: Values and Guardianship</H1>\n<H1>with Lama Shenpen Hookham</H1>\n<H2>19-26 April&nbsp;2008</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><FONT face=Verdana>This retreat is for those who want to enter fully into the life and training within the AHS. It is for those who understand how it is by serving others that our own practice matures and that it is only through the Dharma that we can bring ultimate benefit to ourselves and others. At this retreat Lama Shenpen will introduce and outline her vision for Guardianship training in terms of mandala principle and the living transmission of the Dharma within the Mahamudra and Dzogchen lineage. In particular, we will explore what values Guardians will be training to uphold. From within we want our behaviour to each other and in relation to the mandala to be conducive to Awakening at all times and from outside we want to be seen to stand for Awakening and the welfare and peace of the world.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\n<P>If you would like more information and an application to attend, email&nbsp;<A href="mailto:april@ahs.org.uk">april@ahs.org.uk</A></P>\n<P><FONT color=#191970><STRONG>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</STRONG></FONT></P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;March 1</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>', '2008-04-19T00:00:00'),
(377, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2008-05-24T11:00:00'),
(164, 'The King of Pranidhanas and the Avatamsaka', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week retreat on the Samantabhadracharya Pranidhana and the Avatamsaka Sutra.', '<H1>The King of Pranidhanas and the Avatamsaka</H1>\n<H1>with Lama Shenpen Hookham</H1>\n<H2>21-28 June&nbsp;2008</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana>The June retreat will focus on the Pranidhana section of the Living the Awakened Heart training and in particular on the Samantabhadracharya Pranidhana from the Avatamsaka or Flower Ornament Sutra. Following on from Rigdzin Shikpo''s teachings on the Avatamsaka in November 2007, participants will be expected to familiarise themselves with his booklet on Mahayana Sutra Principles (available from booklets@ahs.org.uk) as well as with the Samantabhadracharaya Pranidhana (text available on <A href="http://www.ahs.org.uk/sanghaspace/ahs/ahs-envivo.asp?ID=1450">Sanghaspace Living the Awakened Heart pages</A>) Students will be expected to review some additional study worksheets in the weeks running up to this retreat. Please book early.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></P>\n<P><FONT color=#191970><STRONG>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</STRONG></FONT></P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;March 1</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>', '2008-06-21T00:00:00'),
(304, 'Trimandala', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2008-07-07T00:00:00'),
(165, 'Mind Training to Awaken the Heart: Lojong Practice', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week training our mind in the practice of exchanging self for other.', '<H1>Mind Training to Awaken the Heart: Lojong Practice</H1>\n<H1>with Lama Shenpen Hookham</H1>\n<H2>16-23 August&nbsp;2008</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Courier New''"><FONT face=Verdana>Lojong means ''training our mind'' and refers to methods of changing our thinking in order to open our heart. To be open hearted is actually our natural way of being, but our ego-centric thinking traps us in a world where we feel we are the ones who are losing out, who&nbsp;are the victims, hurt, deprived, put down, disempowered and so on. Lojong trains us to reverse our way of thinking so that we become more aware of and can more easily let go of our negative frame of mind that prevents us feeling genuine love and compassion for others.<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Courier New''"><FONT face=Verdana>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><FONT face=Verdana><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Trebuchet MS''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Courier New''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">The Lojong method consists of opening out into the formless meditation, practising sending and taking (tonglen) and then applying aphorisms or wise sayings to reflect on and remind us of the practice throughout the day, especially in difficult and challenging situations. Lojong is a very practical discipline</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana>You&nbsp;will be given a reading list in advance of this retreat so that&nbsp;you can&nbsp;come prepared with questions and observations from trying to apply these teachings in practice.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></P>\n<P><FONT color=#191970><STRONG>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</STRONG></FONT></P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;March 1</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>', '2008-08-16T00:00:00'),
(166, 'Trimandala', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week of body awareness practice, meditation and profound teachings on self and other.', '<H1>Trimandala</H1>\n<H1>with Lama Shenpen Hookham</H1>\n<H2>23-30 August&nbsp;2008</H2>\n<H2>Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H2>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana>A week of body awareness practice, meditation and profound teachings on self and other.</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana></FONT></SPAN></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Courier New''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana>You must book early to attend. FINAL BOOKING DATE: July 15 2008</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></P>\n<P><FONT color=#191970><STRONG>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</STRONG></FONT></P>\n<P>This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside with splendid views toward Mount Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic but comfortable, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P>The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or Bangor (20 miles away). You can easily get a taxi or bus to the Hermitage. You will be sent full travel&nbsp;details and information on what to bring when you book. </P>\n<P>Retreats begin on Saturday afternoon with a meeting for newcomers and formally end on the final Saturday morning.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the retreat ending ceremony, there will be a short pilgrimage to a local sacred site. If you are interested in joining the pilgrimage, plan to stay through Saturday evening.</P>\n<P>All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including kitchen help, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.</P>\n<H5>Costs</H5>\n<P>Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P>\n<P>Offerings to&nbsp;Lama Shenpen</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose.&nbsp;Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>Accomodation</P>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P>Single room:&nbsp;┬ú37/night;&nbsp;Shared room: ┬ú32; Camping or off-site: ┬ú22/night</P>\n<P>This amount goes entirely towards the cost of food, running the Hermitage, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. The Sangha does not aim to make any profit on its retreats.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<P>\n<H5>How To Book</H5>\n<P>Places are limited, so please book well in advance, and if possible&nbsp;<B>no later&nbsp;than&nbsp;March 1</B>. You may download a booking form by clicking&nbsp;<A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here</A>.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth, LL52 0RN. You will receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H5>Questions</H5>\n<P>If you have any questions about this retreat, please email events@ahs.org.uk or phone the Sangha office at 01766 523110.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions</A> about retreats or the booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events</A>.</P>\n<H5>Bursaries</H5>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary, email bursaries@ahs.org.uk.</P>\n<H5>Donations to support Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P>The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to.&nbsp; Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, 5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN.</P>', '2008-08-23T00:00:00'),
(378, 'Unknown', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', '', 'Rigdzin Shikpo Rinpoche,Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2008-09-15T18:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(167, 'Trusting the Heart of Buddhism: Month Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A rare opportunity to expand our vision of reality in the context of intensive practice.', '<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN><FONT face=Verdana size=5>Trusting the Heart of Buddhism</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Verdana size=5>with Lama Shenpen Hookham</FONT></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN>Month retreat at the Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face=Arial>4 October&nbsp;to 1 November</FONT></SPAN></FONT></SPAN></H2>\n<H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Times New Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT size=3><FONT face="Trebuchet MS">&nbsp;<IMG src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/hermitage_hills.jpg" align=textTop border=0><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></FONT></FONT></H2><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">At the Heart of Buddhism is a living&nbsp;truth, like a timeless flame waiting to be discovered.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will be the first retreat on <I>Trusting the Heart of Buddhism</I>, which is&nbsp;the follow-on course from <I>Discovering the Heart of Buddhism</I>. Whereas DHB is&nbsp;about our immediate experience THB goes further into exploring how this&nbsp;relates to a vaster vision, the cosmos and the deepest questions about the&nbsp;nature of reality&#151;questions such as: What is Truth? Why are we here? What&nbsp;is the path? Where does it lead? </P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><EM>"At the heart of reality is a hidden truth, which is reflected within each&nbsp;of us, but unrealised. To realise this truth takes courage, persistence and&nbsp;training. It changes our world and ourselves eventually igniting the fire of&nbsp;vision, love and creative power.&nbsp;This truth is not an affair of the intellect, but a living presence that&nbsp;lays a demand for its fulfilment on the totality of our being. The quest for&nbsp;it having begun, we can never give it up or rather it never gives us up."</EM></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Courier New''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; ~ Rigdzin Shikpo</SPAN></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">This retreat is a unique opportunity to&nbsp;devote an extended period of time to&nbsp;our meditation and daily life awareness practice, explore our experience, and sharpen our insight, all in the supportive atmosphere of a group retreat. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The retreat will involve:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Many hours of meditation each day<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">Detailed instructions on the practice of formless meditation</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Reflection on the course materials from Trusting the Heart of Buddhism</SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Teachings and Question &amp; Answer sessions with Lama Shenpen on these topics<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Personal interviews with Lama Shenpen to discuss our meditation and reflection</SPAN></DIV>\n<LI>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">An atmosphere of silence<o:p></o:p></SPAN></DIV></LI></UL>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><FONT color=#000000></FONT>&nbsp;</H4>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Accommodation for the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Although this is a group retreat, most of the meditation periods will be done in retreatants'' own room. Each retreatant will have his or her own room with shared bathroom facilities. While there will be extended periods of solitary meditation and silence, there will also be times when retreatants can connect with their fellow participants and feel the support from others who are doing the same thing. <o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Dharma Work on the retreat</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">All retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to help keep the retreat running, including helping in the kitchen, tending the shrine room, teacher''s attendant, interview organizer, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;A rota will be put up for these tasks.<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4>Do I have to come for all of the retreat?</H4>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Lama Shenpen requests that everyone taking part in the retreat come for the full time if possible, and priority will be given to those booking for the entire retreat. If you cannot come to the whole retreat, and if there is room available,&nbsp; you will be allowed to come for just part, provided you can come for at least 1 week and provided you can be there for the first week. </SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN>&nbsp;</P>\n<H3 class=MsoBodyText style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><FONT size=4>Costs<o:p></o:p></FONT></SPAN></H3>\n<P style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<H4 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">Offering to Lama Shenpen </H4>\n<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">\n<P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. Lama Shenpen will receive no payment for her teaching other than what is given as offerings. Students are asked to make a donation to the Teacher''s Fund, to be used for this purpose. </SPAN><EM>Suggested amount: ┬ú50-200 per week</EM></P></BLOCKQUOTE>\n<H5 class=MsoHeading7 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm">Retreat costs</H5>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 5.55pt 6pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%; tab-stops: 14.2pt 134.7pt">This amount goes entirely towards the cost of running the Hermitage, catering, and offsetting the Sangha''s overheads in running events. Retreat costs may be subject to change.</P></SPAN>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;</SPAN>&nbsp; \n<TABLE style="WIDTH: 425px; HEIGHT: 141px" align=left>\n<TBODY>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Early Bird Discount:&nbsp; </TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú693 if you book by&nbsp;1 August</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;Otherwise:</TD>\n<TD>\n<P>&nbsp;┬ú770/whole month, or<BR>&nbsp;┬ú35/night for the first 7 nights, and <BR>&nbsp;┬ú25/night for subsequent nights</P></TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD>\n<TD>&nbsp;</TD></TR>\n<TR>\n<TD></TD>\n<TD></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 6pt 0.5in; tab-stops: 5.75in">\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: ''Frutiger 55 Roman''; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"></SPAN></SPAN><o:p></o:p></P>&nbsp;<o:p></o:p> \n<P></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<H6>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H6>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H6>&nbsp;</H6>\n<H6>The Hermitage of the Awakened Heart</H6>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">This retreat will be held at the Hermitage, which is on the Llyn peninsula in North Wales, in lovely countryside and with splendid views toward Snowdon. Accommodation at the Hermitage is quite basic, in cottages and caravans.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Travel information</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The nearest train station is Criccieth (4 miles from the Hermitage), or you can take the train to Bangor (20 miles away) and get a taxi or buses to the Hermitage. You will be sent full details of what to bring with you and travel information when you book.</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Note for those&nbsp;considering coming&nbsp;from overseas: the nearest airports are Birmingham and Manchester (2-4 hours by train), but London (Heathrow or Gatwick) (5-7 hours by train) is also possible.</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</H5>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">How to Book</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">There are limited places on this retreat, so please book early. You will receive a substantial discount if you book for the whole month by&nbsp;1 August. <STRONG>The last date we will accept bookings is&nbsp;22 September</STRONG>. You may download a booking form by clicking <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/HermBookingForm2007.doc">here.</A></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"></SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You may&nbsp;request a booking form by emailing <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A> &nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to: Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street, Criccieth LL52 0RN. &nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or putting you on a waiting list or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">If you have any questions about this retreat please email <A href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">events@ahs.org.uk</A>. </P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm -2.85pt 0pt 0cm; LINE-HEIGHT: 110%">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></SPAN></P>\n<UL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0cm" type=circle>\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>.<o:p></o:p></SPAN> \n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></SPAN><B><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><o:p></o:p></SPAN></B></LI></UL>\n<H5 class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt; TEXT-ALIGN: justify"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Bursaries</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary email <A href="mailto:bursaries@ahs.org.uk">bursaries@ahs.org.uk</A> .</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<H5 class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">Donation to Support the Bursary Fund</H5>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">&nbsp;</P>\n<P class=MsoBodyText2 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 0pt">The bursary fund depends on regular donations. Please consider giving something to enable another person to attend this retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount you can offer will be gratefully received. Cheques should be clearly marked for the Bursary Fund, made out to the Shrimala Trust, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office,&nbsp;5A High Street&nbsp;Criccieth LL52 0RN</P></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN>', '2008-10-04T00:00:00'),
(379, 'Meditation workshop', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2008-11-22T10:00:00'),
