(189, 'Jewel Ornament of Liberation', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'This year we are completing the second half of our study of the Jewel Ornament of Liberation by Gampopa. The purpose of focusing on this 12th century text is to understand how the training in the DHB fits with the traditional framework of the Mahayana teachings.', '<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P><STRONG>The Jewel Ornament of Liberation</STRONG></P>\n<P>This year we are completing the second half of our study of the ''Jewel Ornament of Liberation'' by Gampopa. The purpose of focusing on this 12th century text is to understand how the training in the DHB fits in with the traditional framework of the Mahayana teachings. This year we are focusing on the Bodhisattva path and its basis in&nbsp;loving kindness and not clinging to views.&nbsp;&nbsp;Lama Shenpen is&nbsp;strongly encouraging students who wish to attend the June retreat to attend as many of the St Mary''s weekends as they can in order to train in the spirit of the path&nbsp;before going&nbsp;more&nbsp;deeply into its nature and its fruition. There will be an on-line course for&nbsp;the first half of the text for those who missed it last year or who wish to repeat it as well as an on-line course on the second half for those who wish to prepare for the retreat whether they are able to attend it or not.&nbsp;</P>\n<P>To find out more about our Retreats go to <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.com/">www.buddhism-connect.com</A> </P>\n<P>To make payments or donations please go to&nbsp; <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/donations-and-payments/">http://www.buddhism-connect.org/donations-and-payments/</A></P>', '2010-06-17T00:00:00'),
(190, 'Work Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'This is a retreat for anyone that can offer practical help with some of the jobs that need doing at the Hermitage.  There will be several hours of meditation each day as well as the time set aside for work.', '<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P><STRONG>Work Retreat</STRONG></P>\n<P>This is a retreat for anyone that can offer practical help with some of the jobs that need doing at the Hermitage.&nbsp; There will be several hours of meditation each day as well as the time set aside for work.&nbsp; The work will be very varied and nearer the time we will give more information about this.&nbsp; There will be something to suit all skills!</P>\n<P>It is up to you how long you can stay during the month, a few days,&nbsp; a week or the whole month!</P>\n<P>More about this soon.</P>\n<P>If you would like to discuss the possibilty of doing this, please contact <A href="mailto:anne@ahs.org.uk">anne@ahs.org.uk</A> and speak to Tara (Anne)</P>', '2010-07-02T00:00:00'),
(399, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2010-08-21T12:00:00'),
(191, 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism 2', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Following from last years very successful study of DHB1.  The week will be divided between teachings, study and meditation.  For those that are studying DHB it is an oportunity to deepen your understanding and explore how to experience living DHB.', '<table style="height: 498px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="636">\n<tbody>\n<tr align="left" valign="top">\n<td align="left" valign="top" scope="colgroup"><strong><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;">\n<h3><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;"><br /></span></h3>\n</span></strong></td>\n<td colspan="2" valign="top">\n<h2><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;">Discovering the Heart of Buddhism 2:  Transmission</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;">Lama Shenpen</span></span></h3>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr align="left" valign="top">\n<td valign="top"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;">&nbsp;<img style="border-right: 20px solid white; float: left;" title="[19-11-08] lshhead.jpg" src="/resources/images/lshhead.jpg" alt="[19-11-08] lshhead.jpg" width="150" height="200" /></span></td>\n<td colspan="2" valign="top"><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;">\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Verdana;">Although  the process of Awakening is something that happens within us&mdash;and to something  within us&mdash;there is a sense in which it is just as true to say that it comes to  us, as if we were recipients of some kind of gift or power from beyond  ourselves. The process of this inspiration of Awakening passing from one being  to the next is transmission.<span>&nbsp; </span>Transmission is like the igniting of one flame from another&mdash;the living  flame of Awakening to our true nature, the Buddha&rsquo;s Enlightenment. Transmission  is a mysterious, deep and subtle process and begins even in spite of our doubts  and hesitations, even in spite of our not knowing what it means  exactly.</span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Verdana;">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Verdana;">This  retreat is a special opportunity to take an extended period of time to deepen  our meditation and daily life awareness practice, explore our experience, and  sharpen our insight, all in the supportive atmosphere of a group  retreat.</span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 12.6pt 6pt 0in;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;" lang="EN-US">From  Lama Shenpen&rsquo;s <em>&lsquo;Notes on Transmission&rsquo;: </em></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 12.6pt 6pt 0in;"><span style="font-size: x-small;"><em><span lang="EN-US">&lsquo;So the implicit  connection students work with from the beginning of DHB becomes explicit and is  now based on a mutual understanding between myself and the student.&nbsp;As students  open their hearts and formally acknowledge their conviction that they have  glimpsed the base of the path in their own experience, this transmission can  take place. It is pointed to by the DHB and confirms our wish to commit  ourselves to cultivating this by continuing to spiral ever more deeply round and  around the key points expressed in those teachings.&nbsp; The fruit will be the full  realisation of their deepest level of significance as full Awakening. </span></em><em></em></span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 12.6pt 6pt 0in;"><em><span style="font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-family: Verdana;" lang="EN-US">Having  received the transmission you can think of your on-going work on the DHB and THB  as a means of linking into the Mahamudra and Dzogchen transmission lineage  through your direct connection with me.&rsquo;</span><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Verdana;" lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></strong></span></em></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 12.6pt 6pt 0in;">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 12.6pt 6pt 0in;"><em><strong></strong></em></p>\n</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h1>Group Retreats in Wales 2010</h1>\n<p><span style="font-family: verdana,geneva;"><span style="font-size: small;">Group retreats are held at the Hermitage of the  Awakened Heart on the beautiful Llyn Peninsula in North Wales.&nbsp; For details  about the practicalities of going on retreat at the Hermitage, click here. There  is no fixed cost for retreats at the Hermitage--rather we rely on your generous  donations. To register for a retreat or to find out more, email <a href="mailto:events@ahs.org.uk">hermitage@ahs.org.uk</a> . Click here for a <a href="../../../resources/documents/GroupBookingForm2009.doc">booking form</a>.  Click here for a list of <a href="../../../resources/documents/groupretreatpracticalities.doc">practicalities  and a map</a>.</span></span></p>', '2010-08-26T00:00:00'),
(194, 'Windows into Other Worlds', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Teaching,Day', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Lama Shenpen and Aled will be exploring the meeting point of traditional Welsh and Buddhist stories.', '<p>On Friday 17th September at 7.30pm at the Hermitage there will be an evening with Lama Shenpen and Aled Williams entitled " Windows into Other Worlds". They will be exploring the meeting point of traditional Welsh and Buddhist stories, how they can open us up to a greater view of reality and how they may resonate with our lives today.</p>\n<p>Tea and biscuits will be provided after the talk and the cost for attending the evening is &pound;5<br /><br />On Saturday 18th September we will be having another one of our popular open days where you are welcome to join us for a day of silent meditation with teachings from Lama Shenpen and time for questions and discussion. The day will run from 10 am- 5pm with coffee and registration from 9.30am. All refreshments and a vegetarian lunch will be provided and the cost for the day is &pound;20.<br /><br />While these prices will cover our costs any further donations for the teachings and for the Hermitage are always very gratefully received.<br />It is important that everyone who intends to come does book in advance so we know numbers for catering. <br />You are welcome to stay overnight at the Hermitage if you arrange this in advance.</p>\n<p>Email <a href="mailto:hermitage@ahs.org.uk">hermitage@ahs.org.uk</a> <br /></p>', '2010-09-17T00:00:00'),
(400, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2010-09-19T00:00:00'),
(193, 'THB retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Month,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'At this retreat Lama Shenpen will give teachings from Book 2 of Trusting the Heart of Buddhism, which is a follow-on course for students who have completed DHB.', '<p>Even if you have not completed the DHB, this retreat will still be accessible to you. You will be sent some reading to do in advance of the course. Lama Shenpen will be giving teachings during the first two weeks of the retreat. It is possible to come for a few days or a week only, but only if you can be there from the beginning of the retreat. It normally doesn''t work to try to slot it once a retreat has begun. For those who are able to, staying on for the full experience of a month''s retreat is strongly recommended for deepening your understanding and integrating it into your practice.</p>', '2010-11-18T00:00:00'),
(303, 'Role of the teacher', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2010-12-15T00:00:00'),
(401, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2010-12-21T00:00:00'),
(402, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2010-12-30T11:00:00'),
(403, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2011-03-19T11:00:00'),
(204, 'Shrimalagana retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Retreat for Shrimalagfana members', '<p>Retreat for Shrimalagana members.</p>', '2011-04-30T00:00:00'),
(404, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Katie Morrow', '', '', '2011-06-18T11:00:00'),
(202, 'Ratnagotravibhaga Part 1', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Two weeks,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '2 week retreat focusing on the Ratnagotravibhaga', '<p>Lama Shenpen will lead a 2 week retreat focusing on the Ratnagotravibhaga. More information about this event will follow shortly.</p>', '2011-07-09T00:00:00'),
(203, 'Meditation Intensive', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Five Cram,Tara Dew,Jane Powell', 'An opportunity to deepen your practice of meditation in the peaceful atmosphere of the Hermitage.', '<p>An opportunity to deepen your practice of meditation in the peaceful atmosphere of the Hermitage.</p>\n<p>Held mostly in silence, with guidance and teaching, this retreat is suitable for beginners and more experienced meditators alike.</p>\n<p>This week-long retreat will be taught by members of the Teachers Group: Five Cram, Tara and Jane Powell. It will also be possible to have interviews with Lama Shenpen.</p>\n<p>Five writes:</p>\n<p>"Meditation from the Heart" &ndash; Come and get an annual service for your meditation! Tune up the engine of your practice - not so much repairing faults as opening to new possibilities. We''ll work on different approaches that might be helpful in finding that &ldquo;sweet spot&rdquo;. Get under the bonnet with our Mahamudra tool-kit, adjust your samatha and vipashyana. Suitable for all models - old bangers to Formula One.</p>\n<p>For more details and to request a booking form, e-mail <a href="mailto:jane@ahs.org.uk">jane@ahs.org.uk</a>.</p>', '2011-08-13T00:00:00'),
(439, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2011-09-10T11:00:00'),
(205, 'Manifesting the Awakened Mind: Stupa Consecration Event', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham,Lama Phuntsok', 'Special event to consecrate the stupa, with a programme of meditation, teachings and rituals.', '<p>The stupa being constructed at the Hermitage will be consecrated at a special event this October. As Lama Shenpen has described, in the Buddhist tradition stupas are regarded as monuments of immense spiritual power, nexuses of connections that bring down the adhistana of Awakening. Therefore it is regarded as extremely beneficial to have the strong connection that comes from participating in the creation of a stupa by attending the consecration.</p>\n<p>Our visiting Tibetan stupa expert Lama Phuntsok and his 3 assistants will be arriving in the UK on 25th September. They will be firstly completing the stupa at Karma Dechen Choling, Daphne &lsquo;s site near Hay on Wye, before coming to the Hermitage on around 5th October and staying for 7 &ndash; 10 days.</p>\n<p>We are planning for the event to run from Wednesday 5th &ndash; Thursday 13th October, with the main consecration on the full moon of Wednesday 12th. However, we can&rsquo;t make any promises about the timings.</p>\n<p>The event will be a structured programme of meditation, teachings and also assisting in and being present at the rituals involved in the elaborate process of filling and consecrating the stupa.</p>\n<p>As stupas are symbols of the mind of the Buddha, Lama Shenpen will give teachings on &lsquo;Manifesting the Awakened Mind&rsquo;. Lama Phuntsok has offered to give some teachings while he is with us and Lama Rigdzin Shikpo may also be present and may offer to teach us as well.</p>\n<p>Accommodation at the Hermitage will be limited so it is advisable to book soon. Camping is an option and we will also provide a list of local B&amp;Bs and self catering cottages.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Priority for accommodation will be given to those who can attend the whole event. We are able to offer free board and lodging for a few people who are willing to help with organising the event and especially providing hospitality for the Lamas.&nbsp; We are encouraging people to come early &ndash; from 1st October and to stay on after the event to help.</p>\n<p><br />For more information and a booking form please contact Sally Sando at <a href="mailto:princesshenry100@yahoo.com">princesshenry100@yahoo.com</a></p>', '2011-10-05T00:00:00'),
(286, 'Guenon seminars', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2011-11-22T00:00:00'),
(440, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2011-12-10T16:00:00'),
(405, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-01-07T15:00:00'),
(406, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-03-03T11:00:00'),
(226, 'Khenpo Namgyal', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Khenpo Namgyal,Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Love and compassion', '<p>Khenpo teaches on Love and compassion</p>', '2012-04-14T00:00:00'),
(227, 'Shrimalagana retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Teachings,Retreat,Gathering', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Annual Shrimalagana retreat', '<p>Annual SMG retreat</p>', '2012-04-20T00:00:00'),
(213, 'Commited Students Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Teachings,Gathering,Retreat', 'Lama Shenpen', 'A 5 day retreat at The Hermitage for students who would like to deepen their commitment to the Sangha and practice.', '<p><!-- 		@page { margin: 2cm } 		P { margin-bottom: 0.21cm } 	--></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">Have you been working through DHB for at least a year? </span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">Would you like to deepen your connection and express your commitment to the sangha? </span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">Would you like to find out about further opportunities to practice, train and enjoy contact with other committed</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US"> students? </span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">Then please apply to come on this retreat which will be run by the Shrimalagana with input from Lama </span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">Shenpen.</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><!-- 		@page { margin: 2cm } 		P { margin-bottom: 0.21cm } 	--></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">To apply please write to hermitage@ahs.org.uk for more information and an application form. </span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US">All applications must be received by 1st March and there will be a 4 week on line preparation course delivered</span></span></span></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span style="font-family: Arial,serif;"><span style="font-size: small;"><span lang="en-US"> before the retreat.</span></span></span></p>', '2012-04-24T00:00:00'),
(214, 'Communication that is between us - an NVC workshop', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Workshop', 'Patrycja Bielak,Kerry Manson', 'We will be exploring the potential for connection that is hidden in our daily interactions with people.', '<p>We will be exploring the potential for connection that is hidden in our daily interactions with people. We will be addressing both difficult work conversations and tensions with our loved ones around the themes of criticism and anger management. Any interaction can become a deep spiritual lesson about the nature of connection. Have the courage to learn. Have the courage to see Openness, Clarity and Sensitivity between ourselves and others. Cost &pound;50 for the weekend training<br /><br />Patrycja Bielak is a communication trainer (trained in Nonviolent Communication), theatre instructor, trained philosopher (MA) and AHS member.<br />Kerry Manson is a communication trainer (trained in Nonviolent Communication), therapist and psychologist.</p>', '2012-05-05T00:00:00'),
(407, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-05-12T15:00:00'),
(215, 'Introduction to Pastoral Care', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Workshop', 'Mary Waterford', 'We are always looking for ways to support each other better in our Sangha, and now we have an exciting opportunity to get some expert training.', '<p>We are always looking for ways to support each other better in our Sangha, and now we have an exciting opportunity to get some expert training. Mary Waterford is a Clinical Pastoral Education (CPE) Supervisor and coordinator of pastoral care in palliative care in Canberra, and she has offered to run a course at the Hermitage for members of all faith groups well as for Sangha members. The course will be useful for those interested in supporting people within the Sangha or in a professional setting, such as in hospitals and prisons. The final two days will be a working retreat for our Sangha only, where we will look at putting the learning into practice. You can find out more here http://pastoralcareact.org/cpe/default.html or email Shrimala Plumridge on Shrimala@ahs.org.uk.</p>\n<p>14th-18th May for the main course and then 19-20th May for RETREAT into Community for sangha members.</p>\n<p>The cost for the main course is &pound;225 full board, &pound;125 if staying offsite.</p>\n<p>To&nbsp; book, please pay online or by cheque to the office, and e-mail your details to events@ahs.org.uk.</p>', '2012-05-14T00:00:00'),
(408, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-06-09T15:00:00'),
(409, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-06-15T11:00:00'),
(217, 'Ratnagotravibhaga Part 2', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Two weeks,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Lama Shenpen will be leading this retreat which will continue from last year our study of this seminal text on Buddha Nature.', '<p>Lama Shenpen will be leading this retreat which will continue from last year our study of this seminal text on Buddha Nature.</p>', '2012-06-23T00:00:00'),
(410, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-07-14T14:00:00'),
(411, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-08-04T14:00:00'),
(218, 'Moving Body, Still Mind', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Alan Smith', 'a wonderful opportunity to explore the core principles of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism through connecting with the ''felt-wisdom'' of our bodies.', '<p>On this retreat we will use some simple Tai Chi-based movements to release physical tensions and to engage the heart.&nbsp; The retreat will consist of periods of meditation and movement, of stillness and active reflection and is a wonderful opportunity to explore the core principles of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism through connecting with the ''felt-wisdom'' of our bodies. <br /><br />"The freedom offered by the Dharma is constantly manifesting right in front of us. To engage with it requires us to rediscover a child-like simplicity.&nbsp; It is completely simple and yet simple is not the same as easy. This retreat is an invitation to explore deeply with a light touch. To become present through kindness rather than discipline. To move from the heart with presence and dignity and to meet ourselves in another". <br /><br />Requirements for the retreat: Comfortable clothing &amp; flat-soled shoes.&nbsp;&nbsp; Although gentle physical exercises will be involved, no physical struggle or discipline will be necessary.<br />Alan is an AHS teacher and long-term student of Lama Shenpen and Rigdzin Shikpo. He has been teaching Tai Chi, and Chi Kung since 1985.<br />If you have any questions about this retreat, do email Alan on: awakeningheart@talktalk.net or telephone 07722 765009. Please book by 31st May to ensure a place on this retreat.</p>', '2012-08-11T00:00:00'),
(219, 'DHB and Meditation retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen', 'Ideal for those who are new to DHB or if you would like to refresh your practice', '<p>Ideal for those who are new to DHB or if you would like to refresh your practice</p>', '2012-08-18T00:00:00'),
(441, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-09-01T15:00:00'),
(220, 'Five Buddha Families: CANCELLED', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'THIS EVENT IS CANCELLED A retreat led by Lama Shenpen exploring the mandala of the five wisdom energies that provide a complete picture of totality, and relating this to our meditation practice.', '<p>THIS RETREAT HAS BEEN CANCELLED</p>\n<p>A retreat led by Lama Shenpen exploring the mandala of the five wisdom energies that provide a complete picture of totality, and relating this to our meditation practice.</p>', '2012-09-15T00:00:00'),
(412, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2012-09-29T15:00:00'),
(231, 'Hermitage solitary 2012', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', '', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A list of all the retreatants who have been here for solitary in 2012', '<p>A list of those who come to retreat at the hermitage</p>', '2012-10-01T00:00:00'),
(222, 'Self Empathy: Compassion for the life that is me', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Workshop', 'Dorota Godby', '├é┬á"An important area where violence can be replaced with compassion├é┬áis in our moment-to-moment evaluation of ourselves."├é┬áDr M. Rosenberg', '<p>Come and join us in the practice of kindness to self. Experience how self-empathy transforms judgment and opens the door to love and learning. It''s a fun prospect to study self-compassion in community and you are warmly invited. Dorota Godby is a communication trainer, teacher and therapist specialising in gentle effectiveness. She has a passion for elegant, ingenious ways out of pain and loves solutions that satisfy all concerned. She''s been collecting peace-making tools "since always" and recognises Nonviolent Communication as her main inspiration on this journey. Cost &pound;50 for the weekend training</p>', '2012-10-13T00:00:00'),
(442, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Katie Morrow', '', '', '2012-10-27T14:00:00'),
(230, 'Vajrasattva Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Two weeks,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'restricted retreat', '<p>A 2 week retreat led by Lama Shenpen for those who have received the Vajrasattva transmission to talk them further with the sadhana practice</p>', '2012-11-17T00:00:00'),
(250, 'Solitary retreats 2013 at the Hermitage', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', '', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A place to keep all the solitary retreatants in 2013', '<p>Who comes on retreat during the year</p>', '2013-02-14T00:00:00'),
(443, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-02-23T16:00:00'),
(249, 'Alexander technique Day', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Workshop', 'Pippa Bondy', 'A day to explore the fundamentals of the Alexander technique', 'Pippa Bondy is a local Alexander Technique teacher with many years experience. On this day she will explain the principles of the technique and demonstrate it with hands on practice.', '2013-03-02T00:00:00'),
(413, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-03-30T17:00:00'),
(444, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-04-27T15:00:00'),
(232, 'Work Period', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat', '', 'Working together to prepare the Hermitage for the season', 'This will be a five day period to come together as a sangha to help to prepare the Hermitage for the retreat season. the work will involve cleaning and painting the stupa, gardening, treating the wooden buildings, cleaning the shrine room and general cleaning and tidying jobs. There will be morning and evening meditation as usual. This is an opportunity to work together with the Hermitage team, bringing mindfulness into our work and offering our time to nurture the sacred space of the Hermitage.', '2013-05-03T00:00:00'),
(233, 'Shrimalagana Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Teachings,Retreat,Gathering', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A closed retreat for Shrimalagana members', '<p>This week is for Shrimalagana members to come together for practice, for receiving teachings and to continue to develop ways of  connecting with each other and working together  to form a vehicle to uphold the adhistana of the lineage.</p>', '2013-05-09T00:00:00'),
(234, 'Mahayanagana and committed students retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Five days,Teachings,Gathering,Retreat', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Mahayanagana retreat for those in the gana and those intertested in joining', 'This retreat is for all AHS members who are in the Mahayanagana which is a practice circle linked to the full moon feast, and for any who might be interested in joining. If you would like to explore how to take your commitment to the Dharma within this sangha further then do consider coming to this week at the Hermitage. It will be an opportunity to connect to other committed students, to practice together, to receive teachings and to find out about what is on offer within the sangha and what you can do to help. For more information, please contact Tara on tara@ahs.org.uk', '2013-05-18T00:00:00'),
(235, 'Annual Sangha Celebration', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'The annual gathering of the Sangha, where we come together to take or renew our vows, and reflect on death.', '<p>The Annual Sangha Celebration is being held this year for the first time at the Hermitage, and people will be able to take Refuge and Bodhisattva Vows in front of our Stupa.</p>\n<p>If you are thinking of taking Vows and would like to know more, please e-mail Sarah Pink on sarahesp2000@hotmail.com.</p>\n<p>More information will be available nearer the time or from events@ahs.org.uk.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>WE ARE FULLY BOOKED FOR ACCOMMODATION AT THE HERMITAGE.</p>\n<p>If you would still like to come for the day, please email events@ahs.org.uk and we will inform you of alternative arrangements for staying overnight.</p>', '2013-05-24T00:00:00'),
(236, 'Silent retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Five days, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A silent retreat, with teachings.', '<p>This retreat follows on immediately after the Annual Sangha Celebration weekend and is an ideal opportunity for those who have made the journey to the Hermitage to stay on for a while and deepen their practice through meditation and reflection. There will be some teachings and Lama Shenpen will be available for interviews.</p>\n<p><br />To book a place, e-mail events@ahs.org.uk.</p>', '2013-05-27T00:00:00'),
(414, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-06-22T14:00:00'),
(415, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-07-20T14:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(239, 'Family Week', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week', '', 'A time for families to come and be at the Hermitage', '<p>This event is to be confirmed. It is our wish to offer the space of the Hermitage for families this week and to design some activities that will be both fun and have a Dharma content for the children. It will be specifically aimed at primary school age children but all ages are welcome. We hope there will be opportunities also for parents ( and children )to join in meditation sessions. In order for this event to happen we need to know by 1st May if people are interested and what offers of help there are to run the week. It can only go ahead if parents are willing to organize much of the activities, with help from hermitage residents. For more info and to register an interest contact Dashu@ahs.org.uk</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>AS WE CURRENTLY HAVE NO BOOKINGS FOR THIS EVENT, WE ARE EXPECTING TO CANCEL.</p>\n<p>If you would like to come, we may run it as an ''open'' event, which could entail drop-in availability. Please email Dashu@ahs.org.uk to let us know of your interest.</p>', '2013-07-27T00:00:00'),
(240, 'Trimandala Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Agnes Pollner', 'For Agnes and her students', '<p>Malcom. Here is the room allocations so far   \n<table style="height: 50px;" border="0" width="200">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Mh</td>\n<td><br /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Patrycja</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2a</td>\n<td>Dagmar</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2b</td>\n<td>Matthias</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3a</td>\n<td>Heike</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3b</td>\n<td>Monika L</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3c</td>\n<td>Irmgard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>SC</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Sabine and Tamara</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Anne</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Ursula</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>free</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>LC</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1a</td>\n<td>Meike</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1b</td>\n<td>Gisela</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2a</td>\n<td>Agnes D</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2b</td>\n<td>Angelika</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Monika W</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Agnes P</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<br /><br /><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px;"><br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; "><span style="font-size: xx-small;"><br /></span></span></p>', '2013-08-03T00:00:00'),
(241, 'Silent retreat/body awareness', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Five days, Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A silent retreat period with some teachings on body awareness', 'This week will be an opportunity for people to come and do a silent retreat with some input and teachings from Lama Shenpen on body awareness. It could be a good way to lead up to the Discovering the Heart of Buddhism retreat the following week at the Hermitage if you wanted to do both.', '2013-08-11T00:00:00'),
(242, 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Katie Morrow', 'Suitable for new DHB students, those considering doing the course, and for old hands alike.', 'During this week we will explore some of the main themes of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism, touching on Confidence, Heart, Heart Wish, Openness, Clarity, Sensitivity and Mandala Principle, showing how our everyday experience is the gateway through which we can realize our true nature. There will be teachings, sitting and walking meditation, discussion groups, optional body awareness sessions, free time and periods of silence. For more information and to book, contact events@ahs.org.uk.', '2013-08-17T00:00:00'),
(243, 'Progressive Stages of Meditation on Emptiness', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Ten days,Retreat,Teachings', 'Tara Dew,Dashu', 'A guided approach to exploring our experience in meditation in terms of the teachings on emptiness', '<p class="p1">Dashu and I are preparing some materials for the retreat starting on 31<span class="s1"><sup>st</sup></span> August and ending on the morning of Weds 11<span class="s1"><sup>th</sup></span> September.</p>\n<p class="p1">We will be working through the five stages of meditation on emptiness using recorded teachings from Lama Shenpen, transcribed talks and meditation instructions. There will be plenty of opportunity for silent practice and also time for discussion and question and answer sessions.</p>\n<p class="p1">Lama Shenpen is continuing to need a complete rest so we cannot expect her to be involved in the retreat, however it is possible that she may be able to answer some of our questions at some point.</p>\n<p class="p1">To prepare for the retreat it would be good to have read the small book by Khenpo Tsultrim Gyamtso Rinpoche called &lsquo;Progressive Stages of Meditation on Emptiness&rsquo;, translated by Lama Shenpen Hookham. It is available from Wisdom Books. We will be looking at the book during the retreat along with the other materials so there will be the opportunity to look at it in greater depth.</p>\n<p class="p1">Each view could be studied and practised for much longer than we have available on this 10 day retreat, so this can be seen as an introduction to a lifelong process of deepening our meditation practice.</p>\n<p class="p1">&nbsp;</p>', '2013-08-31T00:00:00'),
(257, 'Prayer for realisation', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Lama Shenpen talks about the Prayer for realisation text.', '<p>Part 1- &nbsp;45.50</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cqXMSAnSicY">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cqXMSAnSicY</a></p>\n<p>Part 2 - 55.56</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qbtFzs15DSA&amp;feature=youtu.be">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qbtFzs15DSA&amp;feature=youtu.be</a></p>\n<!--EndFragment-->\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<!--EndFragment-->', '2013-09-24T00:00:00'),
(416, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-10-19T15:00:00'),
(244, 'Guru Rinpoche retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Two weeks,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'xx', '<p>This retreat is only available for invited practitioners.</p>\n<p>If you would like to be invited and haven''t received an invitation, please email tara@ahs.org.uk</p>\n<p>Attendance for first week is compulsary with the second week preferable. If you cannot make it for week one, you will not be accepted on this retreat.</p>\n<p>Other requirements:</p>\n<p>\n<ul>\n<li>Must have listened to Guru Rinpoche recordings form 2007</li>\n<li>Must commit to doing the practice on a regaular basis following the retreat.</li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Please book online.</p>\n<p>If you do not receive a confirmation email - please email Tara@ahs.org.uk for any further details or questions.</p>\n<p><a href="/resources/documents/HermitagePracticalities08.doc">Click Here to download a hermitage practicaltiy sheet for more information on how to get here</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-11-23T00:00:00'),
(417, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2013-12-21T15:00:00'),
(288, 'Singing workshop', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend, Teachings', 'Iegor Reznikoff', '', '', '2014-01-26T00:00:00'),
(289, 'Sadhana of Mahamudra', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-03-17T00:00:00'),
(418, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-03-22T15:00:00'),
(448, 'Dharma & therapy', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Workshop', 'Heinz Roger', '', '', '2014-04-04T21:00:00'),
(419, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-04-19T15:00:00'),
(254, 'Shrimalagana Gathering', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings,Gathering', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Shrimalagana gathering 2014', '<p>Annual SMG gathering</p>', '2014-04-25T00:00:00'),
(255, 'Work Period', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat', '', 'A chance to mix meditation and  helping out with jobs at the Hermitage', '<p>A chance to prepare the hermitage for the events coming up this year. The week will involve a mixture of outdoor and indoor work and there will be plenty of jobs to suit anyone of any fitness and stamina. A fun opportunity to join the Hermitage team in their work and practice.</p>\n<p>There will be morning and evening meditation sessions as ususal.</p>\n<p>The work that you give during the week will be considered as a donation for your stay.</p>\n<p>Please email dashu@ahs.org.uk for more details.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-05-24T00:00:00'),
(420, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-05-24T15:00:00'),
(256, 'Annual Sangha Celebration', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Annual Sangha celebration', '<p>A time for reflection on the year, our lives and a chance to take Refuge and Boddhisattva vows.</p>\n<p>There will be a ceremony on Saturday morning when Lama Shenpen will give Refuge and Bodhisattva vows to those who have requested it in advance. This is followed by a celebratory feast offering and you are invited to bring some buffet style vegetarian food to share. On the Sunday Lama Shenpen will give teachings helping us to reflect on death and this will be followed by a discussion and question and answer session.</p>\n<p>If you would like to take Refuge or the Boddhisattva vow, please email Pema@ahs.org.uk</p>\n<p>All events at the Hermitage are on a donation only basis. We recommend a sliding scale of &pound;15-&pound;45 per day depending on income.&nbsp;<br />You are also invited to make a donation to Lama Shenpen for the teachings she will be giving over the weekend. Suggested amount &pound;30 - 100. Please give according to your means and inspiration.</p>\n<p>Places are limited and we always get fully booked for this event, so it is recommended you book early if you want to stay on-site.</p>\n<p>Camping space is available and there are plenty of campsites and B &amp; B''s locally if there is no room left.</p>\n<p>If you would like to stay on for the Mahayanagana gathering, please book separately and let Dashu know.</p>\n<p><span>PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>You will have to register using the <a href="http://hermitageoftheawakenedheart.org/page5.htm">Hermitage website</a> or our eventbrite page</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/annual-sangha-celebration-registration-11746838109?ref=ebtnebregn" target="_blank"><img src="https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/custombutton?eid=11746838109" alt="Eventbrite - Annual Sangha Celebration" /></a></p>', '2014-06-14T00:00:00'),
(261, 'Mahayanagana Gathering', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Teachings,Retreat,Gathering', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A time for students who are committed to the sangha to meet, practice and discuss how we can take the sangha forward', '<p>This retreat is open to anyone who considers the Awakened Heart Sangha as their spiritual home.&nbsp;In practice this means that it is sutable for members of the sangha who have completed DHB ( or at least sepnt 2 years studying it) and who have been an active part of the sangha for 2 - 3 years. It is a time for committed students to get together to discuss how to support the sangha mandala and to engage more fully with the training and curriculum.It is a great time to connect with others in the sangha as well as practice together.</p>\n<p>We call this a ''gathering'' rather than a retreat, as there is a lighter touch around retreat boudaries and we can have plenty of time to talk and plan for the year ahead.</p>\n<p>The&nbsp;gathering follows directly from the Annual Sangha Celebration, to give people the opportunity of being here over this very special time and take vows if you feel ready and inspired.</p>\n<p>You are encouraged to bring an offering for Lama Shenpen in gratitude for her on-going teachings and guidance. Please give according to your means and inspiration. Suggested amount &pound;50- 250. Sugested donation for the Hermitage is &pound;20 - 50 per day.</p>\n<p>If you would like to come, please email tara@ahs.org.uk and book online here.</p>\n<p>If you would like to take&nbsp;Refuge or Boddhisattva vows, please email Pema@ahs.org.uk who will let Lama Shenpen know and give you any information you might want in advance.</p>\n<p><span>PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></p>', '2014-06-16T00:00:00'),
(262, 'Mahamudra Study', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'This will be a study retreat in preparation for the following Mahamudra Pranidhana retreat in August.', '<p>This month will be dedicated to studying the Mahamudra pranidhana as intensively as possible.</p>\n<p>We will be working through the pranidhana with the guidance of Lama Shenpen and will make the sessions available online as we go - perhaps even broadcasting live as we discuss and practice.</p>\n<p>If you cannot make it to the Hermitage during this month, but would like to come to the reterat in August, you will be required to follow along with the materials as much as you can from home.</p>\n<p>We will record any teachings and make them available for download each day - or week as the case may be.</p>\n<p>We will also broadcast live teachings as they happen, either by streaming them or via a ''Google Hangout'' depending on numbers.</p>\n<p>If you would like to find out how to connect form home, email dashu@ahs.org.uk who will give you instructions.</p>\n<p>I have set the cost as a donation of &pound;20 - however, please feel free to change the amount depending on your inspiration and means.&nbsp;This is such a precious opportunity to receive these teachings from Lama Shenpen that we would like to encourage an attitude of giving generously out of gratitude and to support her on-going teaching activity.</p>\n<p><br />If we get enough people for this type of event, we hope to make it a more regular occurance.&nbsp;</p>', '2014-07-05T00:00:00'),
(421, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-07-14T15:00:00'),
(263, 'Mahamudra Pranidhana', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week retreat following on from the study period in July.', '<p>This retreat will require a commitment to following the study period in July for attendance. Please see the details for the study retreat before booking. It is particularly suitable for students who have completed DHB and THB but anyone is welcome to attend.</p>\n<p>We will receive teachings from Lama Shenpen on the Rangjung Dorje Mahamudra Pranidhana, one of the most important texts in the tradition and one that LamamShenpen translated herself from the Tibetan with the guidance of Bokar Rinpoche.</p>\n<p>If you would like to attend and have been following along with the preparatory study, you are welcome to join us at the Hermitage for what will certainly be an important retreat.</p>\n<p>Suggested donation for Lama Shenpen for this teaching event is &pound;150 - &pound;350</p>\n<p>Suggested donation for your stay at the Hermitage is &pound;20 - 50 per day.</p>\n<p>Please note that these amounts are for guidance only. Please give according to your means and inspiration.</p>\n<p><span>PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></p>', '2014-08-02T00:00:00'),
(266, 'Rejoice in your voice to open the heart', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Agnes Pollner', 'A voice workshop using easy body and breath work to invite our voices to open towards their full vibrancies.', '<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">Breathing and giving voice are elementary to our being, to being alive.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">They connect us with our surroundings, space, other people and deeply root us within ourselves. </span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;"><span style="font-size: small;">When we open to the power of our voice we find how close to our heart it is.</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: small;">By sending it outwards to communicate with others it&acute;s vibration and meaning at the same time moves our own body and soul. Delving into our voices we might experience a vibrant quality connecting us to a deeper level of our being. Space and body is vibrating, sounds and perceptions move and we and others are responding by resonance. </span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic;"><span style="font-size: small;">Voice and breath are integral to all religious practice where its powers are used</span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp; </span></span><span style="font-size: small;">to open our hearts, energise and calm.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">In this workshop we will use easy body and breath work to invite our voices to open towards their full vibrancies. We will explore all kinds of sounds and vocal possibilities, playfully and always ready to listen. Doing this we might become aware of how strongly we are clinging to concepts about voice, how it should be and and what it is that makes a voice good or bad. In the vocal exploration during our time together we will aim to relax around this area more and more and move beyond our concepts of singing beautifully into the direction of giving sound from our hearts letting all colours of the voice flow freely.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">Vocal and body exercises in the group and with a partner will alternate with moments of silence and listening. We will take time to meditate and connect what we found with our practice and the Dharma. Another element of the workshop is sharing our thoughts and insights in feedback circles and mindfull dialogue.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> <span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">The voicework I am offering is deeply rooted in the vocal approach of the Roy-Hart-Theatre and a lifetime of practice. I work as voice trainer and performer mostly in Germany and France. I have been teaching the Dharma since 2008, being a student of Lama Shenpen since 2003 and have incorporated vocal exploration into the retreats I am leading for many years.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">The workshop will run over 3 days&nbsp; (friday - Sunday) but you are welcome to join in for just the 2 days of Saturday and Sunday if you cannot manage the full 3 days.</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">Suggested donation for the teachings is &pound;100, Agnes is keen that everyone is able to come and just give what they feel they can. She would like to offer this workshop as a gift to the Hermitage and friends of the Hermitage. Please bring your offering in cash to give to Agnes. Sugested donation for the Hermitage is &pound;20 - 50 per day. Please note that these figures are for guidance only. Please give according to your means and inspiration.<br /></span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span lang="DE"><span style="font-family: Century Gothic; font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span></span><span>PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>', '2014-08-22T00:00:00'),
(264, 'Discovering the Heart of Buddhism', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week retreat for beginners and experienced practitioners alike', '<p>This is a very special opportunity to attend a retreat on the key principles of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism led by Lama Shenpen. The week will involve a mixture of teachings, discussions, and time for meditation practice and will be held with periods of silence and also time for talking and&nbsp;connecting&nbsp;with each other. Lama Shenpen will be available for perosnal interviews during the week for you to discuss your practice with her.</p>\n<p>This week is also offers the very special and precious opportunity to receive&nbsp; a transmission for the Discovering the Heart of Buddhism from Lama Shenpen</p>\n<p>The retreat is available for anyone who has started studying the DHB, or is thinking of becoming a student. It is also suitable for more experienced students who wish to revisit their study of DHB and go deeper into the materials to yield fresh insights.</p>\n<p>Suggested donation for Lama Shenpen for this teaching event is &pound;150 - &pound;350</p>\n<p>Suggested donation for your stay at the Hermitage is &pound;20 - 50 per day.</p>\n<p>Please note that these amounts are for guidance only. Please give according to your means and inspiration.</p>\n<p><span>PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></p>', '2014-09-06T00:00:00'),
(267, 'Distinguishing Phenomena and Pure Being', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Five days,Teachings', 'Sahle O', 'A chance to study a traditional text attributed to Maitreya with the guidance of visiting teacher Sahle-Au', '<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt;"><strong><em><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 18pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA;"><span style="font-family: Calibri;">Transformation as a path</span></span></em></strong></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>\n<p style="margin: 0cm 0cm 10pt;"><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA;"><span style="font-family: Calibri;">During this program, Diane Denis ( Sahle-Au ) invites you to look at the practical application of Maitreya''s text entitled <em>Distinguishing Phenomena and their true nature</em>. Using Mipham''s commentary and Khenpo Tsultrim Gyamtso Rimpoche''s instructions, we will look more precisely at the development of wisdom. In fact, the main questions this text may be asking you are ''<em>what do you rely on as you walk on this path</em>?&nbsp; Even though the idea of emptiness seems to lead nowhere, we will contemplate how it can become a key on our path of transformation. </span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA;">Diane Denis has been a student of Khenpo Rimpoche since 1992. She studied at Naropa University in Colorado, Rigpe Dorje Institute and Marpa for Translators in Nepal for several years. In 2005 while teaching in France, Rimpoche asked her to teach and encouraged her to pursue her university studies. She recently earned her doctorate degree at the University of Laval in Canada. The subject of her thesis is Maitreya''s Distinguishing phenomena and their nature.</span><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA; mso-fareast-language: FR-CA; mso-no-proof: yes;"> She is a friend and colleague of Lama Shenpen.</span></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA; mso-fareast-language: FR-CA; mso-no-proof: yes;">\n<p><strong>Please bring an offering in cash to be made for Sahle-Au for her teachings. Suggested amount &pound;150 - 350. </strong></p>\n<p><strong>Suggested donation for your stay at the Hermitage is &pound;15 - 45 per day.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please note that these amounts are for guidance only. Please give according to your means and inspiration.</strong></p>\n</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA; mso-fareast-language: FR-CA; mso-no-proof: yes;">PLEASE NOTE: Trains to Criccieth are disrupted for the foreseeable future. Please check with National rail enquiries for information. You might find it easier to go to Bangor and catch a bus from there to Penygroes, Bryncir or Rhoslan. Check with Travel Line Cymru for more details and to plan your journey.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Calibri;"><span lang="EN-CA" style="line-height: 115%; font-size: 12pt; mso-ansi-language: EN-CA; mso-fareast-language: FR-CA; mso-no-proof: yes;"><br /></span></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: small;"> </span></p>', '2014-09-15T00:00:00'),
(422, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-09-27T15:00:00'),
(449, 'Calligraphy', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Talk', 'Tashi Mannox', '', '', '2014-10-05T15:00:00'),
(423, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2014-10-18T15:00:00'),
(268, 'Vajrasattva Retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Two weeks,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A restricted event for students training in sadhana practice with Lama Shenpen', '<p>A 2 week retreat for those students who are engaged in training in sadhana practice. These 2 weks will focus on our deepening exploration of the Vajrasattva and Guru Rinpoche sadhanas and&nbsp; on sadhana practice in general.</p>\n<p>It is strongly encouraged to come for the whole 2 weeks or at least the whole of the first week.</p>\n<p>If you haven''t already attedned such an event please contact Lama Shenpen first to ask if it is appropriate to join.</p>', '2014-11-15T00:00:00'),
(294, 'Meditation day', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-03-14T00:00:00'),
(295, 'Meditation day', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-04-18T00:00:00'),
(272, 'SMG and Inner MYG Gathering', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Teachings,Gathering', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Annual gathering of the committed students  to discuss the future of the sangha as well as an opportunity to practice NVC', '<p>This year the Shrimalagana will hold their annual gathering with members of the Mahayanagana who wish to make a deeper commitment and form the inner Mahayanagana.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The inner Mahayanagana are those who are willing and able to attend the annual gathering of committed students each year at the Hermitage and take responsibility for managing and supporting the Mahayanagana as well as more actively supporting the sangha mandala.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Anyone in the current MYG is welcome to enquire about attending this gathering and becoming part of the inner MYG. The next step is<span>&nbsp;to write an email to Tara. It would be helpful if you could share a bit about why you wish to make this step and if you could include details of your training so far including vows taken and transmissions received if possible.&nbsp;</span><span>Attendance at the 2015 joint gana gathering does not constitute becoming a member of the inner MYG. The inner MYG has not yet actually formed &ndash; it is in process.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoListParagraph"><span></span></p>\n<p class="MsoListParagraph"><span>&nbsp;The gathering starts at 6pm on Friday 24th April. The weekend of 25th and 26th April are a special opportunity to receive NVC training and group work with Kirsten Kristensen who came to teach us last year. Her skills , wealth of experience and warmth led to us inviting her back for more this year. It is an integral part of the gathering and highly recommended.</span></p>\n<p class="MsoListParagraph">The rest of the week will comprise some sessions of joint discussions with both ganas and some sessions of SMG and MYG discussing issues separately. There will be a chance to catch up with sangha developments and see how we can engage with projects if we wish to. There will also be an emphasis on the Lifetime of Practice document and our personal training pathways in the sangha. Lama Shenpen will be very involved in the gathering and there may be some sessions of teaching scheduled.</p>\n<p class="MsoListParagraph">The gathering ends on Saturday 1st May at 10 am and there is the opportunity of staying on for a traditional pilgrimage to a local sacred place</p>\n<p class="MsoListParagraph">For more information on the ganas in general and how to join the Mahayanagana please contact Dashu or Anthony King.</p>', '2015-04-24T00:00:00'),
(297, 'NVC', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Workshop', 'Patrycja Bielak', '', '', '2015-04-25T00:00:00'),
(296, 'Meditation day', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-05-16T00:00:00'),
(273, 'Annual Sangha Celebration', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Our annual Sangha and stupa celebration held at the Hermitage. A chance to take or renew our Refuge and Bodhisattva vows, as well as a time to recognise those who are making the AHS their life-long spiritual home.', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>NOTE: NO MORE ROOMS AVAILABLE</p>\n<p>We are almost fully booked for this year''s celebration.</p>\n<p>There is the possibility of camping or sleeping on the shrine room floor. We have a couple of tents if you do not have your own, if you have any spare matresses that you can bring it would be a great help.</p>\n<p>Please email <a href="mailto:dashu@ahs.org.uk">dashu@ahs.org.uk</a> if you would like to book.</p>\n<p>Or you can stay at a local bed and breakfast - (around &pound;50-&pound;70 per night)</p>\n<p>Please download the updated practicality sheet -&nbsp;<a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/u3d9wsfhgqc4oln/ASC%202015%20Practicalities%20sheet.doc?dl=0">https://www.dropbox.com/s/u3d9wsfhgqc4oln/ASC%202015%20Practicalities%20sheet.doc?dl=0</a></p>\n<p>This year the Annual Sangha Celebration will be immediately followed by a meditation retreat.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Those who are taking vows are particularly encouraged to use this time to practice with each other.</p>\n<p>If you would like to take Refuge or Bodhisattva vows, please contact pema@ahs.org.uk for more details.</p>\n<p>As always, we welcome volunteers to help us set up the retreat - so if you can help by arriving a few days early, we would very much welcome you. Your offer to help would be seen as your donation to the Hermitage.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-05-29T00:00:00'),
(274, 'Formless meditation retreat', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Lama Shenpen will give the transmission for the practice of ''Formless Meditation'' as well as personal meditation instruction.\nThis is a chance for us to simply sit with our practice', '<p>Lama Shenpen will give the transmission for the practice of ''Formless Meditation'' as well as personal meditation instruction.</p>\n<p>This is a chance for us to simply sit with our practice together.</p>\n<p>The retreat begins officially on Monday 1st, but participants are encouraged to join us for the Annual Sangha Celebration the preceeding weekend.</p>\n<p>The retreat officially ends at lunchtime on the 6th June - however, it is traditional for us to celebrate the reterat by going on a pilgrimage to a local hill or mountain together in the afternoon. You are welcome to join us if you are able to.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The cost for the retreat is donation based. Suggested rates: &pound;20-&pound;40 per day. See the practicality sheet for more details.</p>\n<p>You can make a donation here by booking online, either for a full amount or to reserve your place with a deposit. You can complete your donation later or when you arrive at the Hermitage.</p>\n<p>You will also be invited to make an offering to Lama Shenpen as a sign of appreciation and gratitude for bringing us the Dharma.</p>\n<p>Suggested &pound;50-&pound;200</p>\n<p>There will be a collection for a gift for Lama Shenpen and towards the feast offering. Suggested &pound;10-&pound;30</p>\n<p>These offerings can be made in cash or cheque at the Hermitage.</p>\n<p>If you would like to stay on for personal retreat afterwards, please contact Dashu@ahs.org.uk.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-06-01T00:00:00'),
(276, 'Trusting the Heart of Buddhism - online Study', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Online course', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Following from the success of the online Mahamudra study program we are pleased to announce another course.\nTrusting the Heart of Buddhism leads to understanding each of the principles in Discovering the Heart of Buddhism in perhaps entirely new and more profound ways.', '<p>This online course will be given as a series of talks from Lama Shenpen over a 4 week period.</p>\n<p>She will be giving two talks a week on Tuesday and Thursday evenings from 7 - 8.30pm starting on Tuesday 7th July. There will also be question and answer sessions or discussion periods on Saturdays at 5pm where possible</p>\n<p>The talks are streamed live and participation in the online course is necessary for those who wish to come on the retreat in August.</p>\n<p>Lama Shenpen will be giving the THB transmission at the retreat. This is not an annual event and may not come around again for a while. It may also be the first part of two courses, depending on how we structure the course.</p>\n<p>If you would like to have access to the materials, join the course or come on the retreat you will need to make a booking.</p>\n<p>if booking on line please make it clear if you are joining this course from home on-line, or if you intend to come to stay at the Hermitage.</p>\n<p>Contact Dashu for more information dashu@ahs.org.uk</p>\n<p class="p1">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><span class="s1">&nbsp;</span><strong>Dana and Donations&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p class="p2">Lama Shenpen would like to make the teachings available to everyone regardless of their financial situation.</p>\n<p class="p2">This can be done if there are enough people who give generously to cover the costs of running, maintaining and developing the Hermitage as a sacred place dedicated to Dharma practice.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">Suggested donation for a 4 week online course: &pound;50-&pound;200</p>\n<p class="p2">All cheques may be made payable to the Shrimala Trust.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">Donations are also very much welcomed and needed at any time to support the Dharma work of the teachers of the Awakened Heart Sangha, in particular Lama Shenpen, who receive no other income for their teaching activity.All donations are deeply appreciated by Lama Shenpen and all the members and friends of the Awakened Heart Sangha because they encourage and sustain our Dharma activity for the sake of all beings.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>', '2015-07-07T00:00:00'),
(299, 'Foundation mentoring', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-07-15T00:00:00'),
(298, 'Trust', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Series', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-07-29T00:00:00'),
(277, 'Trusting the Heart of Buddhism', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A week of meditation retreat at instruction from Lama Shenpen - taking the principles of Trusting the Heart of Buddhism deeper.', '<p>This retreat will be open to those who have participated in the online study course and will be an intensive retreat with personal meditation instruction form Lama SHenpen.</p>\n<p>Lama Shenpen will also give the transmission for Trusting the Heart of Buddhism - which will become a necessary transmission for those wishing to join the inner Mahayanagana.</p>\n<p>It is recommended that you will have worked on the DHB materials for at least 1 year before looking at THB, though if you are interested, you can discuss it with Lama Shenpen, who may permit you to come.</p>\n<p><strong>Dana and Donations&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p class="p2">Lama Shenpen would like to make the teachings available to everyone regardless of their financial situation. This can be done if there are enough people who give generously to cover the costs of running, maintaining and developing the Hermitage as a sacred place dedicated to Dharma practice. Retreatants like to have some kind of guidance on how much they need to be giving in order to keep the Hermitage afloat. As a rough and ready guide we can usually cover our costs if sufficient retreatants give at the following rates for an overnight stay:&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Generous offering: &pound;45+ per night: </strong>This will allow us to invest in projects to improve the hermitage for future retreats as well as support Hermitage residents and cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Supportive offering: &pound;25-&pound;45 per night: </strong>This will allow us support Hermitage residents as well as subsidise those who cannot afford the full rate and to help us cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Low income offering: &pound;15-&pound;25 per night: </strong>This will help us to support Hermitage residents and cover running costs&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Subsidised offering: up to &pound;15 per night: </strong>We estimate that &pound;15 per night is around the minimum required for us to cover running costs and pay for food during your stay. If you can only afford this level, your stay will be subsidised through the generosity of others who are willing to donate more.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">You will be given a donation form during the retreat to fill in before you leave. All cheques may be made payable to the Shrimala Trust.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">Donations are also very much welcomed and needed at any time to support the Dharma work of the teachers of the Awakened Heart Sangha, in particular Lama Shenpen, who receive no other income for their teaching activity.</p>\n<p class="p2">During the retreat envelopes will be made available for you to make an offering for the teacher which could be made in cash or by cheque (to S.Hookham). Suggested amount &pound;50-&pound;100</p>\n<p class="p2">There will also usually be a collection for the end of retreat feast and for the gift that is presented to the teacher. Suggested Amount &pound;10-30</p>\n<p class="p2">All donations are deeply appreciated by Lama Shenpen and all the members and friends of the Awakened Heart Sangha because they encourage and sustain our Dharma activity for the sake of all beings.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-08-08T00:00:00'),
(302, 'Khenpo Namgyal visit', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Khenpo Namgyal', '', '', '2015-08-16T00:00:00'),
(452, 'Hermitage local group', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Day,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2015-08-22T16:00:00'),
(278, 'Yogic Songs Workshop', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Weekend,Workshop', 'Kristina Bischoff', 'This is an opportunity to work with a professional choir master, who can help us improve our yogic singing.', '<p>The weekend begins on Friday at 6pm and ends on Monday lunchtime. Everyone is warmly invited to attend especially shy singers! We will be singing yogic songs together, doing some vocal exercises, some lujong ( yogic physical exercises) , meditation and some discussion over the meaning of the songs.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="DE">The weekend is led by Kristina Bischoff who we met at Khenpo Rinpoche''s 80th party celebrations inNepal last year. She led a pretty spontaneous choir which was amazing!</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="DE">She writes: - " I have been a student of Dzogchen Ponlop Rinpoche since 1999. In the year 2000 I then met Khenpo Rinpoche. I am singer, a journalist, and have published in the past a Dharma Music CD, that was made with the blessing of the DPR. (Dzogchen Ponlop Rinpoche).&nbsp;</span>In 2005 I opened a Buddhist choir here in Hamburg named &bdquo;Siddha Singers&ldquo;. Its aim was to bring people together, that would like to sing Dharma Songs or Dohas, no matter what tradition they were from On the basis of that former work, in 2012 &nbsp;I started a choir workshop in three centers here in Germany called " Siddha Singers Reloaded&ldquo;.&nbsp;<span>I especially invite shy singers to join in, using advice from P&ouml;nlop Rinpoche, who quotes Karma Chakme on Dohas: " You should sing these songs, no matter how good or bad your voice is. Even if you sound like a howling dog, you should sing and connect with the blessing of the lineage."&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="DE">When there is the opportunity, we even perform what we have learned. &nbsp;</span>In May 2015, we had the great chance to sing for HH the 17th Gyalwang Karmapa during the inauguration of the Stupa at the Kamalashila Institute in Langenfeld, Germany. Check out this Video starting from minute 1.12:&nbsp;<a href="http://m.youtube.com/watch?feature=youtu.be&amp;v=gmM8wIiiEUE">m.youtube.com/watch?feature=youtu.be&amp;v=gmM8wIiiEUE</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;In August of the same year, around 200 visitors of the Dalai Lamas teaching in Hamburg, joined me successfully in a 90 minutes Siddha Singers Workshop. In November 2014, I took the workshop to the United States, joining with singers and practicioners in cities like Boulder, Seattle, New York, Hartford and Philadelphia.</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It should be a fun weekend. Open to all.</p>\n<p>Suggested donation &pound;60-120 as an offering for Kristina.</p>\n<p>Donation to the Hermitage for staying</p>\n<p class="p1">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><span class="s1">&nbsp;</span><strong>Dana and Donations&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p class="p2">Lama Shenpen would like to make the teachings available to everyone regardless of their financial situation. This can be done if there are enough people who give generously to cover the costs of running, maintaining and developing the Hermitage as a sacred place dedicated to Dharma practice. Retreatants like to have some kind of guidance on how much they need to be giving in order to keep the Hermitage afloat. As a rough and ready guide we can usually cover our costs if sufficient retreatants give at the following rates for an overnight stay:&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Generous offering: &pound;45+ per night: </strong>This will allow us to invest in projects to improve the hermitage for future retreats as well as support Hermitage residents and cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Supportive offering: &pound;25-&pound;45 per night: </strong>This will allow us support Hermitage residents as well as subsidise those who cannot afford the full rate and to help us cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Low income offering: &pound;15-&pound;25 per night: </strong>This will help us to support Hermitage residents and cover running costs&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Subsidised offering: up to &pound;15 per night: </strong>We estimate that &pound;15 per night is around the minimum required for us to cover running costs and pay for food during your stay. If you can only afford this level, your stay will be subsidised through the generosity of others who are willing to donate more.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">You will be given a donation form during the retreat to fill in before you leave. All cheques may be made payable to the Shrimala Trust.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">All donations are deeply appreciated by Lama Shenpen and all the members and friends of the Awakened Heart Sangha because they encourage and sustain our Dharma activity for the sake of all beings.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>', '2015-08-28T00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(279, 'Openness and Confidence - DHB Year 2', 'Hermitage of the Awakened Heart, North Wales', 'Week,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Lama Shenpen will continue teaching on the principles of Discovering the Heart of Buddhism', '<p>If you would like to attend this retreat, you are recommended to watch the teaching materials from the retreat in 2014.</p>\n<p>Lama Shenpen will give the DHB transmission - and we will take this opportunity to officially recognise new Members.</p>\n<p>This who were at the retreat are automatically invited. The retreat is a donation only event.</p>\n<p class="p1">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><span class="s1">&nbsp;</span><strong>Dana and Donations&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p class="p2">Lama Shenpen would like to make the teachings available to everyone regardless of their financial situation. This can be done if there are enough people who give generously to cover the costs of running, maintaining and developing the Hermitage as a sacred place dedicated to Dharma practice. Retreatants like to have some kind of guidance on how much they need to be giving in order to keep the Hermitage afloat. As a rough and ready guide we can usually cover our costs if sufficient retreatants give at the following rates for an overnight stay:&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Generous offering: &pound;45+ per night: </strong>This will allow us to invest in projects to improve the hermitage for future retreats as well as support Hermitage residents and cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Supportive offering: &pound;25-&pound;45 per night: </strong>This will allow us support Hermitage residents as well as subsidise those who cannot afford the full rate and to help us cover running costs.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Low income offering: &pound;15-&pound;25 per night: </strong>This will help us to support Hermitage residents and cover running costs&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2"><strong>Subsidised offering: up to &pound;15 per night: </strong>We estimate that&pound;15 per night is around the minimum required for us to cover running costs and pay for food during your stay. If you can only afford this level, your stay will be subsidised through the generosity of others who are willing to donate more.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">You will be given a donation form during the retreat to fill in before you leave. All cheques may be made payable to the Shrimala Trust.&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">Donations are also very much welcomed and needed at any time to support the Dharma work of the teachers of the Awakened Heart Sangha, in particular Lama Shenpen, who receive no other income for their teaching activity. During the retreat envelopes will be made available for you to make an offering for the teacher which could be made in cash or by cheque (to S.Hookham). There will also usually be a collection for the end of retreat feast and for the gift that is presented to the teacher&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">All donations are deeply appreciated by Lama Shenpen and all the members and friends of the Awakened Heart Sangha because they encourage and sustain our Dharma activity for the sake of all beings.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="p2">&nbsp;</p>', '2015-09-12T00:00:00'),
