(208, 'What use am I too others if I''m no use to myself?', 'St Columba''s Centre, Woking, Surrey', 'Weekend,Teachings', 'Tara Dew,Steph Hair,Jane Powell,Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Teaching weekend: What use am I to others if I├óΓé¼Γäóm no use to myself?\nSt Columba├óΓé¼Γäós Retreat Centre, Woking, Surrey\nWith Tara, Steph Hair and Jane Powell (with a teaching to be given by Lama Shenpen)\n\nAre we sometimes less than useful to ourselves? We will be looking at ways we distort or block our path and how to respond to this with kindness, clarity and humour. By exploring enjoyment and self acceptance we may discover how to be of more use to both ourselves and others.\n\nAccommodation is available at St Columba''s.', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: " lang="EN-US">Are we sometimes less than useful to ourselves? We will be looking at ways we distort or block our path and how to respond to this with kindness, clarity and humour. By exploring enjoyment and self acceptance we may discover how to be of more use to both ourselves and others.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: " lang="EN-US">The Shrimala Trust AGM will be held at 6.30pm on the Saturday evening.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: " lang="EN-US">Cost: &pound;35 each day. To book, send an e-mail to events@ahs.org.uk.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal; background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% white;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: " lang="EN-US">Accommodation is available at St Columba''a - please contact jessica@ahs.org.uk for more information.</span></p>', '2012-02-04T00:00:00'),
(245, 'Heart of Meditation', 'St Columba''s Centre, Woking, Surrey', 'Day,Teachings', 'Katie Morrow,Five Cram', 'Meditation course open to all, on 23 Sept, 3 Nov and 8 Dec.', 'This course, which is open to all, moves on from an exploration of sitting meditation, to walking meditation, daily life awareness practice, through to an introduction to the dharmic context for practice and discussion of how to keep one''s practice alive.\n\nFor more details contact info.wokingahsgroup@gmail.com or call Thinley on 01483 564669.', '2012-09-23T00:00:00'),
(320, 'Liberating the heart', 'St Marys Convent, London', 'Weekend,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', '', '', '2002-03-09T00:00:00'),
