iority="64" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium Shading 2 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="65" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium List 1 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="66" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium List 2 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="67" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium Grid 1 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="68" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium Grid 2 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="69" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Medium Grid 3 Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="70" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Dark List Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="71" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful Shading Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="72" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenUsed="false" Name="Colorful List Accent 3" /> <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="73" SemiHidden="false"    UnhideWhenU', '2015-07-10T00:00:00'),
(46, 'Courage of Awakening', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'x', 'x', '2002-08-09T00:00:00'),
(61, 'Aversion', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'How to work with the varieties of aversion, such as anger, impatience and resentment, on the path to Awakening.', 'xxx', '2003-01-24T00:00:00'),
(77, 'The First Step is the Last Step', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Our limited view of the nature of time and space result in a restless ambition to be something else. Dropping this ambition is both the first and last step on the path.', 'The First Step is the Last Step - the timeless nature of the path.&nbsp; Our limited view of the nature of time and space feed our lack of trust about what we are, resulting in a restless ambition to be something else.&nbsp; Dropping this ambition is both the first and last step on the path.', '2004-02-06T00:00:00'),
(97, 'Opening to the Qualities of the Buddha', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Opening to the Qualities of the Buddha.  Exploring what is meant by Buddha, the Awakened One, and the qualities of Awakening, looking at different ways in which we can evoke and link into those qualities in our meditation and daily life awareness practice.', '<P>\n<H1>&nbsp;</H1>\n<H1><IMG height=250 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/priory%20postcard%201.jpg" width=450 align=middle border=0></H1>\n<P>&nbsp;</P>\n<P>The Awakened Heart Sangha will be holding a residential weekend retreat on the theme of ΓÇýOpening to the Qualities of the BuddhaΓÇÖ. Shenpen will explore what is meant by Buddha, the Awakened One and the qualities of Awakening, looking at different ways in which we can evoke and link into those qualities in our meditation and daily life awareness practice.</P>\n<P>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation. There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups.</P>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6pm on Friday evening with a meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7:15pm for everyone. The retreat will end by 4:30pm on Sunday. This weekend offers an opportunity to experience the community provided by a residential retreat, but for a short period. Retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to keep the retreat running, and a rota will be put up. All meals will be fully catered for us, giving us time to enjoy and reflect on the peaceful atmosphere. </P>\n<H3>How to Book</H3>\n<P>Retreats at the Priory fill up quickly, so to avoid disappointment, please book your place early, and <B>NO LATER THAN NOVEMBER 9</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than November 9 be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P>You may download a booking form from this website, by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/Booking%20Form%20Nov%202004%20(single).doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>. </P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Cindy Cooper, 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL</STRONG>. </P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H3>Costs</H3>\n<H4>Offering to Shenpen</H4>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this weekend other than what she is given as offerings.&nbsp; <I>Suggested amount: ┬ú15-┬ú80</I></P>\n<H4>Accommodation and Catering Costs</H4>\n<P>This amount largely goes to the Priory for catering and venue hire.&nbsp; An amount is added to cover basic Sangha overheads, but not to make any profit. </P>\n<P>Single Room:&nbsp;&nbsp;┬ú90/weekend</P>\n<P>Shared Room: ┬ú84/weekend</P>\n<P>Off-site (own accommodation): ┬ú60/weekend </P>\n<H4>Help Run this Retreat </H4>\n<P>A number of people are needed to manage the running of this retreat, and 50%-100% discounts are available. For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact the Events Coordinator, Jane Powell, on 01970 880827, <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</P>\n<H4>Bursaries </H4>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha to help people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL or <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P>\n<H4>Bursary Fund </H4>\n<P>Please consider making a donation to the bursary fund to help someone else attend the retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount will be gratefully received.&nbsp; Your cheque should be made payable to the Shrimala Trust, marked clearly&nbsp; ΓÇýFor the Bursary FundΓÇÖ, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P>\n<H3>The Venue ΓÇô The Priory</H3>\n<P>The weekend will be held at the Priory of our Lady at Sayers Common, which is about 8 miles north of Brighton, set in the peaceful countryside of the Sussex Downs. The Priory is an Augustinian monastic community, which leads the contemplative life while running a pastoral centre for groups or individuals for retreats, conferences or simply periods of peace and quiet. Though the community has a long spiritual tradition, the monastery, pastoral centre and strikingly modern church, which recalls the oast houses of the Weald, are all newly built and very comfortable.</P>\n<P>The nearest rail station to the Priory is Hassocks on the main London-Brighton line; by road it is just off the A23.&nbsp; Full details will be sent to you once you book a place.</P>\n<H3>Questions</H3>\n<P>If you have any questions about this weekend, contact: <STRONG>Cindy Cooper,</STRONG> <STRONG>99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL, tel:&nbsp;(020) 7834 5367,</STRONG>&nbsp;email: <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>.</P>&nbsp; <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/Booking%20Form%20Nov%202004%20(single).doc" target=_blank>Click here for a downloadable booking form</A>. \n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL>', '2004-11-19T00:00:00'),
(104, 'Tonglen', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Tonglen. Introducing the practice of Tonglen as a way of turning towards experience and finding a fresh more compassionate response to our own suffering and the suffering of others.', '<H1>&nbsp;</H1>\n<H1><IMG height=250 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/priory%20postcard%201.jpg" width=450 align=middle border=0></H1>\n<P>The Awakened Heart Sangha will be holding a residential weekend retreat on the theme of ΓÇýTonglen''. Shenpen will introduce the practice of Tonglen as a way of turning towards experience and finding a fresh and more compassionate response&nbsp;to our own suffering and the suffering of others.</P>\n<P>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation. There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups.</P>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6pm on Friday evening with a meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7:15pm for everyone. The retreat will end by 4:30pm on Sunday. This weekend offers an opportunity to experience the community provided by a residential retreat, but for a short period. Retreatants are expected to help with various tasks to keep the retreat running, and a rota will be put up. All meals will be fully catered for us, giving us time to enjoy and reflect on the peaceful atmosphere. </P>\n<H3>How to Book</H3>\n<P>Retreats at the Priory fill up quickly, so to avoid disappointment, please book your place early, and <B>NO LATER THAN JANUARY 25th</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than January 25th be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P>You may download a booking form from this website, by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20feb%202005%20(single).doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>. </P>\n<P>Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Sarah Pink,</STRONG> <STRONG>Gilberts Cottage, Church Road, Farringdon, Alton, GU34 3EG</STRONG>. </P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P>\n<H3>Costs</H3>\n<H4>Offering to Shenpen</H4>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this weekend other than what she is given as offerings.&nbsp; <I>Suggested amount: ┬ú15-┬ú80</I></P>\n<H4>Accommodation and Catering Costs</H4>\n<P>This amount largely goes to the Priory for catering and venue hire.&nbsp; An amount is added to cover basic Sangha overheads, but not to make any profit. </P>\n<P>Single Room:&nbsp;&nbsp;┬ú90/weekend</P>\n<P>Shared Room: ┬ú84/weekend</P>\n<P>Off-site (own accommodation): ┬ú60/weekend </P>\n<H4>Help Run this Retreat </H4>\n<P>A number of people are needed to manage the running of this retreat, and discounts of up to 50%-100%&nbsp;are available. For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact the Events Coordinator, Jane Powell, on 01970 880827, <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</P>\n<H4>Bursaries </H4>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha to help people who would not otherwise be able to attend retreats. To apply for a bursary write to Cindy Cooper at 99 Warwick Way, London SW1V 1QL or <A href="mailto:cindy@ahs.org.uk">cindy@ahs.org.uk</A>, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P>\n<H4>Bursary Fund </H4>\n<P>Please consider making a donation to the bursary fund to help someone else attend the retreat who would not otherwise be able to. Any amount will be gratefully received.&nbsp; Your cheque should be made payable to the Shrimala Trust, marked clearly&nbsp; ΓÇýFor the Bursary FundΓÇÖ, and sent to the Awakened Heart Sangha Office, Bwthyn Plas Brynhir, Lon Ednefyd, Criccieth LL52 0AR.</P>\n<H3>The Venue ΓÇô The Priory</H3>\n<P>The weekend will be held at the Priory of our Lady at Sayers Common, which is about 8 miles north of Brighton, set in the peaceful countryside of the Sussex Downs. The Priory is an Augustinian monastic community, which leads the contemplative life while running a pastoral centre for groups or individuals for retreats, conferences or simply periods of peace and quiet. Though the community has a long spiritual tradition, the monastery, pastoral centre and strikingly modern church, which recalls the oast houses of the Weald, are all newly built and very comfortable.</P>\n<P>The nearest rail station to the Priory is Hassocks on the main London-Brighton line; by road it is just off the A23.&nbsp; Full details will be sent to you once you book a place.</P>\n<H3>Questions</H3>\n<P>If you have any questions about this weekend, contact <STRONG>Sarah Pink,</STRONG> <STRONG>Gilberts Cottage, Church Road, Farringdon, Alton, GU34</STRONG> <STRONG>3EG,</STRONG> <STRONG>Tel:(01420) 588477</STRONG>, email: <A href="mailto:sarahesp2000@hotmail.com">sarahesp2000@hotmail.com</A>.</P>\n<P>&nbsp; <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/booking%20form%20feb%202005%20(single).doc" target=_blank>Click here for a downloadable booking form</A>. </P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL>', '2005-02-04T00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `event` (`Id`, `Title`, `field_venue`, `field_event_tags`, `field_leader`, `body`, `B`, `field_datetime`) VALUES
(123, 'Unending and Equal Love for All Beings', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'A weekend retreat where we will explore limitless love, particularly in terms of the practice of the four Apramanas, for which Lama Shenpen will give the transmission and relate this to Tonglen practice.', '<P><IMG height=150 src="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/images/priory%20postcard%201.jpg" width=300 align=centre=0></P>\n<P></P><FONT size=1>\n<P align=justify></P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Theme</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P align=justify>The theme of this weekend retreat will be ''Unending and Equal Love for All Beings''. We shall be exploring limitless love, particularly in terms of the practice of the four Apramanas, for which Lama Shenpen will give the transmission and relate this to Tonglen practice.</P>\n<P align=justify>In addition to the teachings, there will be plenty of sitting and walking meditation. There will be times for silence and times for talking with other retreatants, both informally and in discussion groups. There will also be an opportunity for each retreatant to have an individual interview with Lama Shenpen.</P>\n<P>This retreat will not only increase our understanding of the Apramanas, but will also enrich our Tonglen practice. If you''d like to prepare for this retreat by refreshing your appreciation of Tonglen, you could access Lama Shenpen''s teachings on it by visiting the following link; <FONT color=#0000cd>http://www.ahs.org.uk/sanghaspace/ahs/ahs-envivo.asp?ID=948&amp;Event=104.</FONT></P></FONT></FONT><FONT size=1><FONT face="Lucida Sans" color=#0000cd size=2>\n<P><STRONG>Arrival and Departure Times</STRONG></P></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>The retreat will begin at 6pm on Friday, February 17th with a special meeting for any newcomers, followed by supper at 7 pm for everyone. The retreat will end by 4.30pm on Sunday, February 19<SUP>th</SUP>.</P>\n<P><STRONG><FONT color=#0000cd>Costs</FONT></STRONG></P><B><FONT size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Offering to Lama Shenpen</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>It is traditional to make an offering to Buddhist teachers to express gratitude for teachings received and to make a strong positive connection. All students are asked to make a donation as an offering for Lama Shenpen, who will receive no payment for this week other than what she is given as offerings. <I>Suggested amount:</FONT><FONT size=1> </FONT><FONT size=1>┬ú15-┬ú80</FONT></I></P><FONT size=1><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P><FONT color=#0000cd><EM>Accommodation and Catering Costs</EM></FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P><EM>This amount largely goes to the Priory for catering and venue hire. A small amount is added to cover basic Sangha overheads, but not to make any profit.</EM></P>\n<P><EM>Single(standard): ┬ú90/weekend</EM></P>\n<P><EM>Shared(standard): ┬ú84/weekend</EM></P>\n<P><EM>Own accom(off-site): ┬ú60/weekend</EM></P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><EM><FONT color=#0000cd>Bursary Fund</FONT> </EM></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>There is a bursary fund in the Awakened Heart Sangha that helps people attend retreats who would not otherwise be able to. To apply for a bursary write to Belinda Wain, Llwyn Eilian, Rhosgadfan, Caernarfon, Gwynedd, LL54 7HE or email belinda@ahs.org.uk, explaining your circumstances and what you can afford to pay.</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Help run this retreat</FONT> </P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>A number of people are needed to manage the running of this retreat. For more information and to apply for a position, please mark the booking form or contact the Events Coordinator, Jane Powell, on 01970 880827, <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</P><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Venue &#150; the Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>The weekend will be held at the Priory of Our Lady, Sayers Common, Sussex, 8 miles north of Brighton, set in the peaceful countryside of the Sussex Downs. The Priory is an Augustinian monastic community in contemplative life whilst running a pastoral centre for groups or individuals for retreats, conferences or periods of peace and quiet. The nearest rail station to the priory is Hassocks on the main London-Brighton line; by road it is just off the A23. Full details will be sent to you once you book.</P>\n<H3 class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">How To Book</H3>\n<P>Please book your place early, and if possible <B>NO LATER THAN February 7th</B>.</P>\n<P>While we try to accept late bookings, they are very disruptive to the cooks and organisers of the retreat. Meals have to be planned, food bought, accommodation worked out based on the sex ratio and names already listed. If you try to book any later than February 7th, be prepared to miss the retreat even if there are places available, since it may be too difficult for us to coordinate arrangements.</P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">You may download a booking form from this website by <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/media/events/priory%20bkg%20form%20web.doc" target=_blank>clicking here</A>. </P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt"></P>\n<P class=MsoHeading8 style="MARGIN: 0cm 0cm 6pt">Send your completed form along with your deposit cheque to <STRONG>Belinda Wain, Llwyn Eilian, Rhosgadfan, Caernarfon, Gwynedd, LL54 7HE</STRONG>.</P>\n<P>You will then receive a letter confirming your place and giving you further information about the retreat, or returning your deposit if your booking can not be accepted.</P><FONT size=1><B><FONT face="Lucida Sans" size=2>\n<P align=justify><FONT color=#0000cd>Questions</FONT></P></B></FONT><FONT size=1>\n<P>If you have any questions about the retreat you can contact Jane Powell by phone on 01970 880827 or at Cynefin, Capel Bangor, Aberystwyth, Ceredigion, SY23 3LU or email: <A href="mailto:jpowell@ukonline.co.uk">jpowell@ukonline.co.uk</A>.</P>\n<P>If you are new to Awakened Heart Sangha retreats, you may also want to look at:</P>\n<UL>\n<LI><A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=943">Frequently Asked Questions about retreats</A>. \n<LI>The booklet <A href="http://www.buddhism-connect.org/default.asp?action=article&amp;ID=942">"An Introduction to Awakened Heart Sangha Events".</A></LI></UL></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT></FONT>sights &amp; guidance.', '2006-02-17T00:00:00'),
(134, 'Waiting list: Unending & Equal love...', 'The Priory, Sayers Common, Sussex', 'Weekend,Retreat,Teachings', 'Lama Shenpen Hookham', 'Waiting list for the Feb Priory retreat', '<P>The February Priory retreat is now full.</P>\n<P>Any subsequent bookings to be entered onto this waiting list for any last minute cancellations.</P>', '2006-02-17T00:00:00'),
